11366 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11367 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11368 bool array::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype) const noexcept
11369 {
11370 if (elems_.empty())
11371 return false;
11372
11373 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11374 ntype = elems_[0]->type();
11375
11376 for (const auto& val : elems_)
11377 if (val->type() != ntype)
11378 return false;
11379
11380 return true;
11381 }
11382
11383 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11384 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11385 bool array::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, node * &first_nonmatch) noexcept
11386 {
11387 if (elems_.empty())
11388 {
11389 first_nonmatch = {};
11390 return false;
11391 }
11392 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11393 ntype = elems_[0]->type();
11394 for (const auto& val : elems_)
11395 {
11396 if (val->type() != ntype)
11397 {
11398 first_nonmatch = val.get();
11399 return false;
11400 }
11401 }
11402 return true;
11403 }
11404
11405 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11406 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11407 bool array::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, const node * &first_nonmatch) const noexcept
11408 {
11409 node* fnm = nullptr;
11410 const auto result = const_cast<array&>(*this).is_homogeneous(ntype, fnm);
11411 first_nonmatch = fnm;
11412 return result;
11413 }

11461
11462 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11463 size_t array::total_leaf_count() const noexcept
11464 {
11465 size_t leaves{};
11466 for (size_t i = 0, e = elems_.size(); i < e; i++)
11467 {
11468 auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array();
11469 leaves += arr ? arr->total_leaf_count() : size_t{ 1 };
11470 }
11471 return leaves;
11472 }
11473
11474 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11475 void array::flatten_child(array && child, size_t & dest_index) noexcept
11476 {
11477 for (size_t i = 0, e = child.size(); i < e; i++)
11478 {
11479 auto type = child.elems_[i]->type();
11480 if (type == node_type::array)
11481 {
11482 array& arr = *reinterpret_cast<array*>(child.elems_[i].get());
11483 if (!arr.empty())
11484 flatten_child(std::move(arr), dest_index);
11485 }
11486 else
11487 elems_[dest_index++] = std::move(child.elems_[i]);
11488 }
11489 }
11490
11491 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11492 array & array::flatten()&
11493 {
11494 if (elems_.empty())
11495 return *this;
11496
11497 bool requires_flattening = false;
11498 size_t size_after_flattening = elems_.size();
11499 for (size_t i = elems_.size(); i-- > 0u;)
11500 {
11501 auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array();
11502 if (!arr)
11503 continue;
11504 size_after_flattening--; // discount the array itself
11505 const auto leaf_count = arr->total_leaf_count();
11506 if (leaf_count > 0u)
11507 {
11508 requires_flattening = true;
11509 size_after_flattening += leaf_count;
11510 }
11511 else
11512 elems_.erase(elems_.cbegin() + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(i));
11513 }
11514
11515 if (!requires_flattening)
11516 return *this;
11517
11518 elems_.reserve(size_after_flattening);
11519
11520 size_t i = 0;
11521 while (i < elems_.size())
11522 {
11523 auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array();
11524 if (!arr)
11525 {
11526 i++;
11527 continue;
11528 }
11529
11530 impl::node_ptr arr_storage = std::move(elems_[i]);
11531 const auto leaf_count = arr->total_leaf_count();
11532 if (leaf_count > 1u)
11533 preinsertion_resize(i + 1u, leaf_count - 1u);
11534 flatten_child(std::move(*arr), i); // increments i
11535 }
11536
11537 return *this;
11538 }
11539
11540 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11541 array & array::prune(bool recursive) & noexcept
11542 {
11543 if (elems_.empty())
11544 return *this;
11545
11546 for (size_t i = elems_.size(); i-- > 0u;)
11547 {
11548 if (auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array())
11549 {
11550 if (recursive)
11551 arr->prune(true);
11552 if (arr->empty())
11553 elems_.erase(elems_.cbegin() + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(i));
11554 }
11555 else if (auto tbl = elems_[i]->as_table())
11556 {
11557 if (recursive)
11558 tbl->prune(true);
11559 if (tbl->empty())
11560 elems_.erase(elems_.cbegin() + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(i));
11561 }
11562 }
11563
11564 return *this;
11565 }
11566
11567 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11568 void array::pop_back() noexcept
11569 {
11570 elems_.pop_back();
11571 }
11572
11573 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11574 void array::clear() noexcept
11575 {
11576 elems_.clear();
11577 }
11578
11579 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11580 bool TOML_CALLCONV array::equal(const array & lhs, const array & rhs) noexcept
11581 {
11582 if (&lhs == &rhs)
11583 return true;
11584 if (lhs.elems_.size() != rhs.elems_.size())
11585 return false;
11586 for (size_t i = 0, e = lhs.elems_.size(); i < e; i++)
11587 {
11588 const auto lhs_type = lhs.elems_[i]->type();
11589 const node& rhs_ = *rhs.elems_[i];
11590 const auto rhs_type = rhs_.type();
11591 if (lhs_type != rhs_type)
11592 return false;
11593
11594 const bool equal = lhs.elems_[i]->visit(
11595 [&](const auto& lhs_) noexcept
11596 { return lhs_ == *reinterpret_cast<std::remove_reference_t<decltype(lhs_)>*>(&rhs_); });
11597 if (!equal)
11598 return false;
11599 }
11600 return true;
11601 }
11602}
11603TOML_NAMESPACE_END;
11604

11606#pragma pop_macro("min")
11607#pragma pop_macro("max")
11608#pragma inline_recursion(off)
11609#endif

11638#endif

11641 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11642 table::table(const impl::table_init_pair * b, const impl::table_init_pair * e)
11643 {
11644#if TOML_LIFETIME_HOOKS
11645 TOML_TABLE_CREATED;
11646#endif
11647
11648 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(b);
11649 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(e);
11650 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(b <= e);
11651
11652 if TOML_UNLIKELY(b == e)
11653 return;
11654
11655 for (; b != e; b++)
11656 {
11657 if (!b->value) // empty node_views
11658 continue;
11659
11660 map_.insert_or_assign(std::move(b->key), std::move(b->value));
11661 }
11662 }
11663
11664 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11665 table::table(const table & other) //
11666 : node(other),
11667 inline_{ other.inline_ }
11668 {
11669 for (auto&& [k, v] : other.map_)
11670 map_.emplace_hint(map_.end(), k, impl::make_node(*v));
11671
11672#if TOML_LIFETIME_HOOKS
11673 TOML_TABLE_CREATED;
11674#endif
11675 }

11679 : node(std::move(other)),
11680 map_{ std::move(other.map_) },
11681 inline_{ other.inline_ }
11682 {
11683#if TOML_LIFETIME_HOOKS
11684 TOML_TABLE_CREATED;
11685#endif
11686 }

11690 {

11692 {
11693 node::operator=(rhs);
11694 map_.clear();
11695 for (auto&& [k, v] : rhs.map_)
11696 map_.emplace_hint(map_.end(), k, impl::make_node(*v));
11697 inline_ = rhs.inline_;
11698 }
11699 return *this;
11700 }

11706 {
11707 node::operator=(std::move(rhs));
11708 map_ = std::move(rhs.map_);
11709 inline_ = rhs.inline_;
11710 }
11711 return *this;
11712 }

11714 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11715 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11716 bool table::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype) const noexcept
11717 {
11718 if (map_.empty())
11719 return false;
11720
11721 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11722 ntype = map_.cbegin()->second->type();
11723
11724 for (auto&& [k, v] : map_)
11725 {
11726 TOML_UNUSED(k);
11727 if (v->type() != ntype)
11728 return false;
11729 }
11730
11731 return true;
11732 }
11733
11734 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11735 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11736 bool table::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, node * &first_nonmatch) noexcept
11737 {
11738 if (map_.empty())
11739 {
11740 first_nonmatch = {};
11741 return false;
11742 }
11743 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11744 ntype = map_.cbegin()->second->type();
11745 for (const auto& [k, v] : map_)
11746 {
11747 TOML_UNUSED(k);
11748 if (v->type() != ntype)
11749 {
11750 first_nonmatch = v.get();
11751 return false;
11752 }
11753 }
11754 return true;
11755 }
11756
11757 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11758 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11759 bool table::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, const node * &first_nonmatch) const noexcept
11760 {
11761 node* fnm = nullptr;
11762 const auto result = const_cast<table&>(*this).is_homogeneous(ntype, fnm);
11763 first_nonmatch = fnm;
11764 return result;
11765 }

11772 return it->second.get();
11773 return nullptr;

11778 {

11780
11781#if TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS
11782
11783 if (!n)
11784 {
11785 auto err = "key '"s;
11786 err.append(key);
11787 err.append("' not found in table"sv);
11788 throw std::out_of_range{ err };
11789 }
11790
11791#else
11792
11793 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(n && "key not found in table!");
11794
11795#endif
11796
11797 return *n;
11798 }

11833 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11834 size_t table::erase(std::string_view key) noexcept
11835 {
11836 if (auto it = map_.find(key); it != map_.end())
11837 {
11838 map_.erase(it);
11839 return size_t{ 1 };
11840 }
11841 return size_t{};
11842 }
11843
11844 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11845 table & table::prune(bool recursive) & noexcept
11846 {
11847 if (map_.empty())
11848 return *this;
11849
11850 for (auto it = map_.begin(); it != map_.end();)
11851 {
11852 if (auto arr = it->second->as_array())
11853 {
11854 if (recursive)
11855 arr->prune(true);
11856
11857 if (arr->empty())
11858 {
11859 it = map_.erase(it);
11860 continue;
11861 }
11862 }
11863 else if (auto tbl = it->second->as_table())
11864 {
11865 if (recursive)
11866 tbl->prune(true);
11867
11868 if (tbl->empty())
11869 {
11870 it = map_.erase(it);
11871 continue;
11872 }
11873 }
11874 it++;
11875 }
11876
11877 return *this;
11878 }
11879
11880 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11881 void table::clear() noexcept
11882 {
11883 map_.clear();
11884 }
11885
11886 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11887 table::map_iterator table::insert_with_hint(const_iterator hint, key && k, impl::node_ptr && v)
11888 {
11889 return map_.emplace_hint(const_map_iterator{ hint }, std::move(k), std::move(v));
11890 }
11891
11892 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11893 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11894 bool TOML_CALLCONV table::equal(const table & lhs, const table & rhs) noexcept
11895 {
11896 if (&lhs == &rhs)
11897 return true;
11898 if (lhs.map_.size() != rhs.map_.size())
11899 return false;
11900
11901 for (auto l = lhs.map_.begin(), r = rhs.map_.begin(), e = lhs.map_.end(); l != e; l++, r++)
11902 {
11903 if (l->first != r->first)
11904 return false;
11905
11906 const auto lhs_type = l->second->type();
11907 const node& rhs_ = *r->second;
11908 const auto rhs_type = rhs_.type();
11909 if (lhs_type != rhs_type)
11910 return false;
11911
11912 const bool equal = l->second->visit(
11913 [&](const auto& lhs_) noexcept
11914 { return lhs_ == *reinterpret_cast<std::remove_reference_t<decltype(lhs_)>*>(&rhs_); });
11915 if (!equal)
11916 return false;
11917 }
11918 return true;
11919 }
11920}

11972TOML_IMPL_NAMESPACE_START
11973{
11974 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11975 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11976 bool is_ascii(const char* str, size_t len) noexcept
11977 {
11978 const char* const end = str + len;
11979
11980#if TOML_HAS_SSE2 && (128 % CHAR_BIT) == 0
11981 {
11982 constexpr size_t chars_per_vector = 128u / CHAR_BIT;
11983
11984 if (const size_t simdable = len - (len % chars_per_vector))
11985 {
11986 __m128i mask = _mm_setzero_si128();
11987 for (const char* const e = str + simdable; str < e; str += chars_per_vector)
11988 {
11989 const __m128i current_bytes = _mm_loadu_si128(reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(str));
11990 mask = _mm_or_si128(mask, current_bytes);
11991 }
11992 const __m128i has_error = _mm_cmpgt_epi8(_mm_setzero_si128(), mask);
11993
11994#if TOML_HAS_SSE4_1
11995 if (!_mm_testz_si128(has_error, has_error))
11996 return false;
11997#else
11998 if (_mm_movemask_epi8(_mm_cmpeq_epi8(has_error, _mm_setzero_si128())) != 0xFFFF)
11999 return false;
12000#endif
12001 }
12002 }
12003#endif
12004
12005 for (; str < end; str++)
12006 if (static_cast<unsigned char>(*str) > 127u)
12007 return false;
12008
12009 return true;
12010 }
12011}

12036#endif

12047TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_START
12048{
12049 template <typename T>
12050 class utf8_byte_stream;
12051
12052 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
12053 constexpr auto utf8_byte_order_mark = "\xEF\xBB\xBF"sv;
12054
12055 template <typename Char>
12056 class utf8_byte_stream<std::basic_string_view<Char>>
12057 {
12058 static_assert(sizeof(Char) == 1);
12059
12060 private:
12061 std::basic_string_view<Char> source_;
12062 size_t position_ = {};
12063
12064 public:
12065 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12066 explicit constexpr utf8_byte_stream(std::basic_string_view<Char> sv) noexcept //
12067 : source_{ sv }
12068 {
12069 // skip bom
12070 if (source_.length() >= 3u && memcmp(utf8_byte_order_mark.data(), source_.data(), 3u) == 0)
12071 position_ += 3u;
12072 }
12073
12074 TOML_CONST_INLINE_GETTER
12075 constexpr bool error() const noexcept
12076 {
12077 return false;
12078 }
12079
12080 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12081 constexpr bool eof() const noexcept
12082 {
12083 return position_ >= source_.length();
12084 }
12085
12086 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12087 explicit constexpr operator bool() const noexcept
12088 {
12089 return !eof();
12090 }
12091
12092 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12093 constexpr bool peek_eof() const noexcept
12094 {
12095 return eof();
12096 }
12097
12098 TOML_NODISCARD
12099 TOML_ATTR(nonnull)
12100 size_t operator()(void* dest, size_t num) noexcept
12101 {
12102 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!eof());
12103
12104 num = impl::min(position_ + num, source_.length()) - position_;
12105 std::memcpy(dest, source_.data() + position_, num);
12106 position_ += num;
12107 return num;
12108 }
12109 };
12110
12111 template <>
12112 class utf8_byte_stream<std::istream>
12113 {
12114 private:
12115 std::istream* source_;
12116
12117 public:
12118 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12119 explicit utf8_byte_stream(std::istream& stream) noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) //
12120 : source_{ &stream }
12121 {
12122 if (!*this) // eof, bad
12123 return;
12124
12125 const auto initial_pos = source_->tellg();
12126 char bom[3];
12127 source_->read(bom, 3);
12128 if (source_->bad() || (source_->gcount() == 3 && memcmp(utf8_byte_order_mark.data(), bom, 3u) == 0))
12129 return;
12130
12131 source_->clear();
12132 source_->seekg(initial_pos, std::istream::beg);
12133 }
12134
12135 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12136 bool error() const noexcept
12137 {
12138 return !!(source_->rdstate() & std::istream::badbit);
12139 }
12140
12141 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12142 bool eof() const noexcept
12143 {
12144 return !!(source_->rdstate() & std::istream::eofbit);
12145 }
12146
12147 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12148 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
12149 {
12150 return !(source_->rdstate() & (std::istream::badbit | std::istream::eofbit));
12151 }
12152
12153 TOML_NODISCARD
12154 bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12155 {
12156 return eof() || source_->peek() == std::istream::traits_type::eof();
12157 }
12158
12159 TOML_NODISCARD
12160 TOML_ATTR(nonnull)
12161 size_t operator()(void* dest, size_t num) noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12162 {
12163 TOML_ASSERT(*this);
12164
12165 source_->read(static_cast<char*>(dest), static_cast<std::streamsize>(num));
12166 return static_cast<size_t>(source_->gcount());
12167 }
12168 };
12169
12170 struct utf8_codepoint
12171 {
12172 char32_t value;
12173 char bytes[4];
12174 size_t count;
12175 source_position position;
12176
12177 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12178 constexpr operator const char32_t& () const noexcept
12179 {
12180 return value;
12181 }
12182
12183 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12184 constexpr const char32_t& operator*() const noexcept
12185 {
12186 return value;
12187 }
12188 };
12189 static_assert(std::is_trivial_v<utf8_codepoint>);
12190 static_assert(std::is_standard_layout_v<utf8_codepoint>);
12191
12192 struct TOML_ABSTRACT_INTERFACE utf8_reader_interface
12193 {
12194 TOML_NODISCARD
12195 virtual const source_path_ptr& source_path() const noexcept = 0;
12196
12197 TOML_NODISCARD
12198 virtual const utf8_codepoint* read_next() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) = 0;
12199
12200 TOML_NODISCARD
12201 virtual bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) = 0;
12202
12203#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12204
12205 TOML_NODISCARD
12206 virtual optional<parse_error>&& error() noexcept = 0;
12207
12208#endif
12209
12210 virtual ~utf8_reader_interface() noexcept = default;
12211 };
12212
12213#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12214#define utf8_reader_error(...) throw parse_error(__VA_ARGS__)
12215#define utf8_reader_return_after_error(...) static_assert(true)
12216#define utf8_reader_error_check(...) static_assert(true)
12217#else
12218#define utf8_reader_error(...) err_.emplace(__VA_ARGS__)
12219#define utf8_reader_return_after_error(...) return __VA_ARGS__
12220#define utf8_reader_error_check(...) \
12221 do \
12222 { \
12223 if TOML_UNLIKELY(err_) \
12224 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12225 } \
12226 while (false)
12227
12228#endif
12229
12230#if defined(__APPLE__) || defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__MINGW64__)
12231#define TOML_OVERALIGNED
12232#else
12233#define TOML_OVERALIGNED alignas(32)
12234#endif
12235
12236 template <typename T>
12237 class TOML_EMPTY_BASES utf8_reader final : public utf8_reader_interface
12238 {
12239 private:
12240 static constexpr size_t block_capacity = 32;
12241 utf8_byte_stream<T> stream_;
12242 source_position next_pos_ = { 1, 1 };
12243
12244 impl::utf8_decoder decoder_;
12245 struct currently_decoding_t
12246 {
12247 char bytes[4];
12248 size_t count;
12249 } currently_decoding_;
12250
12251 struct codepoints_t
12252 {
12253 TOML_OVERALIGNED utf8_codepoint buffer[block_capacity];
12254 size_t current;
12255 size_t count;
12256 } codepoints_;
12257
12258 source_path_ptr source_path_;
12259
12260#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12261 optional<parse_error> err_;
12262#endif
12263
12264 bool read_next_block() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12265 {
12266 TOML_ASSERT(stream_);
12267
12268 TOML_OVERALIGNED char raw_bytes[block_capacity];
12269 size_t raw_bytes_read;
12270
12271 // read the next raw (encoded) block in from the stream
12272 if constexpr (noexcept(stream_(raw_bytes, block_capacity)) || !TOML_EXCEPTIONS)
12273 {
12274 raw_bytes_read = stream_(raw_bytes, block_capacity);
12275 }
12276#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12277 else
12278 {
12279 try
12280 {
12281 raw_bytes_read = stream_(raw_bytes, block_capacity);
12282 }
12283 catch (const std::exception& exc)
12284 {
12285 throw parse_error{ exc.what(), next_pos_, source_path_ };
12286 }
12287 catch (...)
12288 {
12289 throw parse_error{ "An unspecified error occurred", next_pos_, source_path_ };
12290 }
12291 }
12292#endif // TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12293
12294 // handle a zero-byte read
12295 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!raw_bytes_read)
12296 {
12297 if (stream_.eof())
12298 {
12299 // EOF only sets the error state if the decoder wants more input, otherwise
12300 // a zero-byte read might have just caused the underlying stream to realize it's exhaused and set
12301 // the EOF flag, and that's totally fine
12302 if (decoder_.needs_more_input())
12303 utf8_reader_error("Encountered EOF during incomplete utf-8 code point sequence",
12304 next_pos_,
12305 source_path_);
12306 }
12307 else
12308 {
12309 utf8_reader_error("Reading from the underlying stream failed - zero bytes read",
12310 next_pos_,
12311 source_path_);
12312 }
12313 return false;
12314 }
12315
12316 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(raw_bytes_read);
12317 std::memset(&codepoints_, 0, sizeof(codepoints_));
12318
12319 // helper for calculating decoded codepoint line+cols
12320 const auto calc_positions = [&]() noexcept
12321 {
12322 for (size_t i = 0; i < codepoints_.count; i++)
12323 {
12324 auto& cp = codepoints_.buffer[i];
12325 cp.position = next_pos_;
12326
12327 if (cp == U'\n')
12328 {
12329 next_pos_.line++;
12330 next_pos_.column = source_index{ 1 };
12331 }
12332 else
12333 next_pos_.column++;
12334 }
12335 };
12336
12337 // decide whether we need to use the UTF-8 decoder or if we can treat this block as plain ASCII
12338 const auto ascii_fast_path = !decoder_.needs_more_input() && impl::is_ascii(raw_bytes, raw_bytes_read);
12339
12340 // ASCII fast-path
12341 if (ascii_fast_path)
12342 {
12343 decoder_.reset();
12344 currently_decoding_.count = {};
12345
12346 codepoints_.count = raw_bytes_read;
12347 for (size_t i = 0; i < codepoints_.count; i++)
12348 {
12349 auto& cp = codepoints_.buffer[i];
12350 cp.value = static_cast<char32_t>(raw_bytes[i]);
12351 cp.bytes[0] = raw_bytes[i];
12352 cp.count = 1u;
12353 }
12354 }
12355
12356 // UTF-8 slow-path
12357 else
12358 {
12359 // helper for getting precise error location
12360 const auto error_pos = [&]() noexcept -> const source_position&
12361 { //
12362 return codepoints_.count ? codepoints_.buffer[codepoints_.count - 1u].position : next_pos_;
12363 };
12364
12365 for (size_t i = 0; i < raw_bytes_read; i++)
12366 {
12367 decoder_(static_cast<uint8_t>(raw_bytes[i]));
12368 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder_.error())
12369 {
12370 calc_positions();
12371 utf8_reader_error("Encountered invalid utf-8 sequence", error_pos(), source_path_);
12372 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12373 }
12374
12375 currently_decoding_.bytes[currently_decoding_.count++] = raw_bytes[i];
12376
12377 if (decoder_.has_code_point())
12378 {
12379 auto& cp = codepoints_.buffer[codepoints_.count++];
12380
12381 cp.value = decoder_.codepoint;
12382 cp.count = currently_decoding_.count;
12383 std::memcpy(cp.bytes, currently_decoding_.bytes, currently_decoding_.count);
12384 currently_decoding_.count = {};
12385 }
12386 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(currently_decoding_.count == 4u)
12387 {
12388 calc_positions();
12389 utf8_reader_error("Encountered overlong utf-8 sequence", error_pos(), source_path_);
12390 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12391 }
12392 }
12393 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder_.needs_more_input() && stream_.eof())
12394 {
12395 calc_positions();
12396 utf8_reader_error("Encountered EOF during incomplete utf-8 code point sequence",
12397 error_pos(),
12398 source_path_);
12399 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12400 }
12401 }
12402
12403 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.count);
12404 calc_positions();
12405
12406 // handle general I/O errors
12407 // (down here so the next_pos_ benefits from calc_positions())
12408 if TOML_UNLIKELY(stream_.error())
12409 {
12410 utf8_reader_error("An I/O error occurred while reading from the underlying stream",
12411 next_pos_,
12412 source_path_);
12413 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12414 }
12415
12416 return true;
12417 }
12418
12419 public:
12420 template <typename U, typename String = std::string_view>
12421 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12422 explicit utf8_reader(U&& source, String&& source_path = {}) noexcept(
12423 std::is_nothrow_constructible_v<utf8_byte_stream<T>, U&&>)
12424 : stream_{ static_cast<U&&>(source) }
12425 {
12426 currently_decoding_.count = {};
12427
12428 codepoints_.current = {};
12429 codepoints_.count = {};
12430
12431 if (!source_path.empty())
12432 source_path_ = std::make_shared<const std::string>(static_cast<String&&>(source_path));
12433 }
12434
12435 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12436 const source_path_ptr& source_path() const noexcept final
12437 {
12438 return source_path_;
12439 }
12440
12441 TOML_NODISCARD
12442 const utf8_codepoint* read_next() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) final
12443 {
12444 utf8_reader_error_check({});
12445
12446 if (codepoints_.current == codepoints_.count)
12447 {
12448 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!stream_ || !read_next_block())
12449 return nullptr;
12450
12451 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!codepoints_.current);
12452 }
12453 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.count);
12454 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.count <= block_capacity);
12455 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.current < codepoints_.count);
12456
12457 return &codepoints_.buffer[codepoints_.current++];
12458 }
12459
12460 TOML_NODISCARD
12461 bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) final
12462 {
12463 return stream_.peek_eof();
12464 }
12465
12466#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12467
12468 TOML_NODISCARD
12469 optional<parse_error>&& error() noexcept final
12470 {
12471 return std::move(err_);
12472 }
12473
12474#endif
12475 };

12478 utf8_reader(std::basic_string_view<Char>, std::string_view) -> utf8_reader<std::basic_string_view<Char>>;
12479 template <typename Char>
12480 utf8_reader(std::basic_string_view<Char>, std::string&&) -> utf8_reader<std::basic_string_view<Char>>;
12481 template <typename Char>
12482 utf8_reader(std::basic_istream<Char>&, std::string_view) -> utf8_reader<std::basic_istream<Char>>;
12483 template <typename Char>

12486#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12487#define utf8_buffered_reader_error_check(...) static_assert(true)
12488#else
12489#define utf8_buffered_reader_error_check(...) \
12490 do \
12491 { \
12492 if TOML_UNLIKELY(reader_.error()) \
12493 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12494 } \
12495 while (false)
12496
12497#endif
12498
12499 class TOML_EMPTY_BASES utf8_buffered_reader
12500 {
12501 public:
12502 static constexpr size_t max_history_length = 128;
12503
12504 private:
12505 static constexpr size_t history_buffer_size = max_history_length - 1; //'head' is stored in the reader
12506 utf8_reader_interface& reader_;
12507 struct
12508 {
12509 utf8_codepoint buffer[history_buffer_size];
12510 size_t count, first;
12511 } history_ = {};
12512 const utf8_codepoint* head_ = {};
12513 size_t negative_offset_ = {};
12514
12515 public:
12516 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12517 explicit utf8_buffered_reader(utf8_reader_interface& reader) noexcept //
12518 : reader_{ reader }
12519 {}
12520
12521 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12522 const source_path_ptr& source_path() const noexcept
12523 {
12524 return reader_.source_path();
12525 }
12526
12527 TOML_NODISCARD
12528 const utf8_codepoint* read_next() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12529 {
12530 utf8_buffered_reader_error_check({});
12531
12532 if (negative_offset_)
12533 {
12534 negative_offset_--;
12535
12536 // an entry negative offset of 1 just means "replay the current head"
12537 if (!negative_offset_)
12538 return head_;
12539
12540 // otherwise step back into the history buffer
12541 else
12542 return history_.buffer
12543 + ((history_.first + history_.count - negative_offset_) % history_buffer_size);
12544 }
12545 else
12546 {
12547 // first character read from stream
12548 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!history_.count && !head_)
12549 head_ = reader_.read_next();
12550
12551 // subsequent characters and not eof
12552 else if (head_)
12553 {
12554 if TOML_UNLIKELY(history_.count < history_buffer_size)
12555 history_.buffer[history_.count++] = *head_;
12556 else
12557 history_.buffer[(history_.first++ + history_buffer_size) % history_buffer_size] = *head_;
12558
12559 head_ = reader_.read_next();
12560 }
12561
12562 return head_;
12563 }
12564 }
12565
12566 TOML_NODISCARD
12567 const utf8_codepoint* step_back(size_t count) noexcept
12568 {
12569 utf8_buffered_reader_error_check({});
12570
12571 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(history_.count);
12572 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(negative_offset_ + count <= history_.count);
12573
12574 negative_offset_ += count;
12575
12576 return negative_offset_
12577 ? history_.buffer + ((history_.first + history_.count - negative_offset_) % history_buffer_size)
12578 : head_;
12579 }
12580
12581 TOML_NODISCARD
12582 bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12583 {
12584 return reader_.peek_eof();
12585 }
12586
12587#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12588
12589 TOML_NODISCARD
12590 optional<parse_error>&& error() noexcept
12591 {
12592 return reader_.error();
12593 }
12594
12595#endif
12596 };
12597}

12684
12685 TOML_PURE_GETTER
12686 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
12687 std::string_view to_sv(const utf8_codepoint& cp) noexcept
12688 {
12689 if (cp.value <= U'\x1F')
12690 return impl::control_char_escapes[cp.value];
12691 else if (cp.value == U'\x7F')
12692 return "\\u007F"sv;
12693 else
12694 return std::string_view{ cp.bytes, cp.count };
12695 }

12700 {

12702 return to_sv(*cp);
12703 return ""sv;
12704 }

12706 struct escaped_codepoint
12707 {
12708 const utf8_codepoint& cp;
12709 };
12710
12711 template <typename T>
12712 TOML_ATTR(nonnull)
12713 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
12714 void concatenate(char*& write_pos, char* const buf_end, const T& arg) noexcept
12715 {
12716 if TOML_UNLIKELY(write_pos >= buf_end)
12717 return;
12718
12719 using arg_type = impl::remove_cvref<T>;
12720
12721 // string views
12722 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<arg_type, std::string_view>)
12723 {
12724 const auto max_chars = static_cast<size_t>(buf_end - write_pos);
12725 const auto len = max_chars < arg.length() ? max_chars : arg.length();
12726 std::memcpy(write_pos, arg.data(), len);
12727 write_pos += len;
12728 }
12729
12730 // doubles
12731 else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<arg_type, double>)
12732 {
12733#if TOML_FLOAT_CHARCONV
12734 const auto result = std::to_chars(write_pos, buf_end, arg);
12735 write_pos = result.ptr;
12736#else
12737 std::ostringstream ss;
12738 ss.imbue(std::locale::classic());
12739 ss.precision(std::numeric_limits<arg_type>::max_digits10);
12740 ss << arg;
12741 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, to_sv(std::move(ss).str()));
12742#endif
12743 }
12744
12745 // 64-bit integers
12746 else if constexpr (impl::is_one_of<arg_type, int64_t, uint64_t>)
12747 {
12748#if TOML_INT_CHARCONV
12749 const auto result = std::to_chars(write_pos, buf_end, arg);
12750 write_pos = result.ptr;
12751#else
12752 std::ostringstream ss;
12753 ss.imbue(std::locale::classic());
12754 using cast_type = std::conditional_t<std::is_signed_v<arg_type>, int64_t, uint64_t>;
12755 ss << static_cast<cast_type>(arg);
12756 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, to_sv(std::move(ss).str()));
12757#endif
12758 }
12759
12760 // escaped_codepoint
12761 else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<arg_type, escaped_codepoint>)
12762 {
12763 if (arg.cp.value <= U'\x7F')
12764 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, to_sv(arg.cp));
12765 else
12766 {
12767 auto val = static_cast<uint_least32_t>(arg.cp.value);
12768 const auto digits = val > 0xFFFFu ? 8u : 4u;
12769 constexpr auto mask = uint_least32_t{ 0xFu };
12770 char buf[10] = { '\\', digits > 4 ? 'U' : 'u' };
12771 for (auto i = 2u + digits; i-- > 2u;)
12772 {
12773 const auto hexdig = val & mask;
12774 buf[i] = static_cast<char>(hexdig >= 0xAu ? ('A' + (hexdig - 0xAu)) : ('0' + hexdig));
12775 val >>= 4;
12776 }
12777 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, std::string_view{ buf, digits + 2u });
12778 }
12779 }
12780
12781 // all other floats (fallback - coerce to double)
12782 else if constexpr (std::is_floating_point_v<arg_type>)
12783 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, static_cast<double>(arg));
12784
12785 // all other integers (fallback - coerce to (u)int64_t)
12786 else if constexpr (std::is_arithmetic_v<arg_type> && std::is_integral_v<arg_type>)
12787 {
12788 using cast_type = std::conditional_t<std::is_unsigned_v<arg_type>, uint64_t, int64_t>;
12789 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, static_cast<cast_type>(arg));
12790 }
12791
12792 else
12793 {
12794 static_assert(
12795 impl::dependent_false<T>,
12796 "concatenate() inputs are limited to std::string_views, integers, floats, and escaped_codepoint");
12797 }
12798 }
12799
12800 struct error_builder
12801 {
12802 static constexpr std::size_t buf_size = 512;
12803 char buf[buf_size];
12804 char* write_pos = buf;
12805 char* const max_write_pos = buf + (buf_size - std::size_t{ 1 }); // allow for null terminator
12806
12807 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12808 error_builder(std::string_view scope) noexcept
12809 {
12810 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, "Error while parsing "sv);
12811 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, scope);
12812 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, ": "sv);
12813 }
12814
12815 template <typename T>
12816 void append(const T& arg) noexcept
12817 {
12818 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, arg);
12819 }
12820
12821 TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
12822 auto finish(const source_position& pos, const source_path_ptr& source_path) const
12823 {
12824 *write_pos = '\0';
12825
12826#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12827 throw parse_error{ buf, pos, source_path };
12828#else
12829 return parse_error{ std::string(buf, static_cast<size_t>(write_pos - buf)), pos, source_path };
12830#endif
12831 }
12832
12833 TOML_DELETE_DEFAULTS(error_builder);
12834 };

12860 struct parse_key_buffer
12861 {
12862 std::string buffer;
12863 std::vector<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> segments;
12864 std::vector<source_position> starts;
12865 std::vector<source_position> ends;
12866
12867 void clear() noexcept
12868 {
12869 buffer.clear();
12870 segments.clear();
12871 starts.clear();
12872 ends.clear();
12873 }
12874
12875 void push_back(std::string_view segment, source_position b, source_position e)
12876 {
12877 segments.push_back({ buffer.length(), segment.length() });
12878 buffer.append(segment);
12879 starts.push_back(b);
12880 ends.push_back(e);
12881 }
12882
12883 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12884 std::string_view operator[](size_t i) const noexcept
12885 {
12886 return std::string_view{ buffer.c_str() + segments[i].first, segments[i].second };
12887 }
12888
12889 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12890 std::string_view back() const noexcept
12891 {
12892 return (*this)[segments.size() - 1u];
12893 }
12894
12895 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12896 bool empty() const noexcept
12897 {
12898 return segments.empty();
12899 }
12900
12901 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12902 size_t size() const noexcept
12903 {
12904 return segments.size();
12905 }
12906 };

12954#if 1 // parser helper macros
12955
12956// Q: "what the fuck is this? MACROS????"
12957// A: The parser needs to work in exceptionless mode (returning error objects directly)
12958// and exception mode (reporting parse failures by throwing). Two totally different control flows.
12959// These macros encapsulate the differences between the two modes so I can write code code
12960// as though I was only targeting one mode and not want yeet myself into the sun.
12961// They're all #undef'd at the bottom of the parser's implementation so they should be harmless outside
12962// of toml++.
12963
12964#define is_eof() !cp
12965#define assert_not_eof() TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(cp != nullptr)
12966#define return_if_eof(...) \
12967 do \
12968 { \
12969 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof()) \
12970 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12971 } \
12972 while (false)
12973
12974#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12975#define is_error() false
12976#define return_after_error(...) TOML_UNREACHABLE
12977#define assert_not_error() static_assert(true)
12978#define return_if_error(...) static_assert(true)
12979#define return_if_error_or_eof(...) return_if_eof(__VA_ARGS__)
12980#else
12981#define is_error() !!err
12982#define return_after_error(...) return __VA_ARGS__
12983#define assert_not_error() TOML_ASSERT(!is_error())
12984#define return_if_error(...) \
12985 do \
12986 { \
12987 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_error()) \
12988 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12989 } \
12990 while (false)
12991#define return_if_error_or_eof(...) \
12992 do \
12993 { \
12994 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof() || is_error()) \
12995 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12996 } \
12997 while (false)
12998#endif
12999
13000#if defined(TOML_BREAK_AT_PARSE_ERRORS) && TOML_BREAK_AT_PARSE_ERRORS
13001#if defined(__has_builtin)
13002#if __has_builtin(__builtin_debugtrap)
13003#define parse_error_break() __builtin_debugtrap()
13004#elif __has_builtin(__debugbreak)
13005#define parse_error_break() __debugbreak()
13006#endif
13007#endif
13008#ifndef parse_error_break
13009#if TOML_MSVC || TOML_ICC
13010#define parse_error_break() __debugbreak()
13011#else
13012#define parse_error_break() TOML_ASSERT(false)
13013#endif
13014#endif
13015#else
13016#define parse_error_break() static_assert(true)
13017#endif
13018
13019#define set_error_and_return(ret, ...) \
13020 do \
13021 { \
13022 if (!is_error()) \
13023 set_error(__VA_ARGS__); \
13024 return_after_error(ret); \
13025 } \
13026 while (false)
13027
13028#define set_error_and_return_default(...) set_error_and_return({}, __VA_ARGS__)
13029
13030#define set_error_and_return_if_eof(...) \
13031 do \
13032 { \
13033 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof()) \
13034 set_error_and_return(__VA_ARGS__, "encountered end-of-file"sv); \
13035 } \
13036 while (false)
13037
13038#define advance_and_return_if_error(...) \
13039 do \
13040 { \
13041 assert_not_eof(); \
13042 advance(); \
13043 return_if_error(__VA_ARGS__); \
13044 } \
13045 while (false)
13046
13047#define advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof(...) \
13048 do \
13049 { \
13050 assert_not_eof(); \
13051 advance(); \
13052 return_if_error(__VA_ARGS__); \
13053 set_error_and_return_if_eof(__VA_ARGS__); \
13054 } \
13055 while (false)
13056
13057#endif // parser helper macros
13058
13059TOML_IMPL_NAMESPACE_START
13060{
13061 TOML_ABI_NAMESPACE_BOOL(TOML_EXCEPTIONS, impl_ex, impl_noex);
13062
13063 class parser
13064 {
13065 private:
13066 static constexpr size_t max_nested_values = TOML_MAX_NESTED_VALUES;
13067
13068 utf8_buffered_reader reader;
13069 table root;
13070 source_position prev_pos = { 1, 1 };
13071 const utf8_codepoint* cp = {};
13072 std::vector<table*> implicit_tables;
13073 std::vector<table*> dotted_key_tables;
13074 std::vector<table*> open_inline_tables;
13075 std::vector<array*> table_arrays;
13076 parse_key_buffer key_buffer;
13077 std::string string_buffer;
13078 std::string recording_buffer; // for diagnostics
13079 bool recording = false, recording_whitespace = true;
13080 std::string_view current_scope;
13081 size_t nested_values = {};
13082#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
13083 mutable optional<parse_error> err;
13084#endif
13085
13086 TOML_NODISCARD
13087 source_position current_position(source_index fallback_offset = 0) const noexcept
13088 {
13089 if (!is_eof())
13090 return cp->position;
13091 return { prev_pos.line, static_cast<source_index>(prev_pos.column + fallback_offset) };
13092 }
13093
13094 template <typename... T>
13095 TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
13096 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13097 void set_error_at(source_position pos, const T&... reason) const
13098 {
13099 static_assert(sizeof...(T) > 0);
13100 return_if_error();
13101
13102 error_builder builder{ current_scope };
13103 (builder.append(reason), ...);
13104
13105 parse_error_break();
13106
13107#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
13108 builder.finish(pos, reader.source_path());
13109#else
13110 err.emplace(builder.finish(pos, reader.source_path()));
13111#endif
13112 }
13113
13114 template <typename... T>
13115 TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
13116 void set_error(const T&... reason) const
13117 {
13118 set_error_at(current_position(1), reason...);
13119 }
13120
13121 void go_back(size_t count = 1) noexcept
13122 {
13123 return_if_error();
13124 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(count);
13125
13126 cp = reader.step_back(count);
13127 prev_pos = cp->position;
13128 }
13129
13130 void advance()
13131 {
13132 return_if_error();
13133 assert_not_eof();
13134
13135 prev_pos = cp->position;
13136 cp = reader.read_next();
13137
13138#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
13139 if (reader.error())
13140 {
13141 err = std::move(reader.error());
13142 return;
13143 }
13144#endif
13145
13146 if (recording && !is_eof())
13147 {
13148 if (recording_whitespace || !is_whitespace(*cp))
13149 recording_buffer.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13150 }
13151 }
13152
13153 void start_recording(bool include_current = true) noexcept
13154 {
13155 return_if_error();
13156
13157 recording = true;
13158 recording_whitespace = true;
13159 recording_buffer.clear();
13160 if (include_current && !is_eof())
13161 recording_buffer.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13162 }
13163
13164 void stop_recording(size_t pop_bytes = 0) noexcept
13165 {
13166 return_if_error();
13167
13168 recording = false;
13169 if (pop_bytes)
13170 {
13171 if (pop_bytes >= recording_buffer.length())
13172 recording_buffer.clear();
13173 else if (pop_bytes == 1u)
13174 recording_buffer.pop_back();
13175 else
13176 recording_buffer.erase(recording_buffer.begin()
13177 + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(recording_buffer.length() - pop_bytes),
13178 recording_buffer.end());
13179 }
13180 }
13181
13182 bool consume_leading_whitespace()
13183 {
13184 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13185
13186 bool consumed = false;
13187 while (!is_eof() && is_horizontal_whitespace(*cp))
13188 {
13189 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!is_ascii_horizontal_whitespace(*cp))
13190 set_error_and_return_default("expected space or tab, saw '"sv, escaped_codepoint{ *cp }, "'"sv);
13191
13192 consumed = true;
13193 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13194 }
13195 return consumed;
13196 }
13197
13198 bool consume_line_break()
13199 {
13200 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13201
13202 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_match(*cp, U'\v', U'\f'))
13203 set_error_and_return_default(
13204 R"(vertical tabs '\v' and form-feeds '\f' are not legal line breaks in TOML)"sv);
13205
13206 if (*cp == U'\r')
13207 {
13208 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip \r
13209
13210 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof())
13211 set_error_and_return_default("expected '\\n' after '\\r', saw EOF"sv);
13212
13213 if TOML_UNLIKELY(*cp != U'\n')
13214 set_error_and_return_default("expected '\\n' after '\\r', saw '"sv,
13215 escaped_codepoint{ *cp },
13216 "'"sv);
13217 }
13218 else if (*cp != U'\n')
13219 return false;
13220
13221 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip \n
13222 return true;
13223 }
13224
13225 bool consume_rest_of_line()
13226 {
13227 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13228
13229 do
13230 {
13231 if (is_ascii_vertical_whitespace(*cp))
13232 return consume_line_break();
13233 else
13234 advance();
13235 return_if_error({});
13236 } while (!is_eof());
13237
13238 return true;
13239 }
13240
13241 bool consume_comment()
13242 {
13243 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13244
13245 if (*cp != U'#')
13246 return false;
13247
13248 push_parse_scope("comment"sv);
13249
13250 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the '#'
13251
13252 while (!is_eof())
13253 {
13254 if (consume_line_break())
13255 return true;
13256 return_if_error({});
13257
13258#if TOML_LANG_AT_LEAST(1, 0, 0)
13259
13260 // toml/issues/567 (disallow non-TAB control characters in comments)
13261 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_nontab_control_character(*cp))
13262 set_error_and_return_default(
13263 "control characters other than TAB (U+0009) are explicitly prohibited in comments"sv);
13264
13265 // toml/pull/720 (disallow surrogates in comments)
13266 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(*cp))
13267 set_error_and_return_default(
13268 "unicode surrogates (U+D800 to U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited in comments"sv);
13269#endif
13270
13271 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13272 }
13273
13274 return true;
13275 }
13276
13277 TOML_NODISCARD
13278 bool consume_expected_sequence(std::u32string_view seq)
13279 {
13280 return_if_error({});
13281 TOML_ASSERT(!seq.empty());
13282
13283 for (auto c : seq)
13284 {
13285 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13286 if (*cp != c)
13287 return false;
13288 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13289 }
13290 return true;
13291 }
13292
13293 template <typename T>
13294 TOML_NODISCARD
13295 bool consume_digit_sequence(T* digits, size_t len)
13296 {
13297 return_if_error({});
13298 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(digits);
13299 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(len);
13300
13301 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++)
13302 {
13303 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13304 if (!is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13305 return false;
13306
13307 digits[i] = static_cast<T>(*cp - U'0');
13308 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13309 }
13310 return true;
13311 }
13312
13313 template <typename T>
13314 TOML_NODISCARD
13315 size_t consume_variable_length_digit_sequence(T* buffer, size_t max_len)
13316 {
13317 return_if_error({});
13318 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(buffer);
13319 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(max_len);
13320
13321 size_t i = {};
13322 for (; i < max_len; i++)
13323 {
13324 if (is_eof() || !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13325 break;
13326
13327 buffer[i] = static_cast<T>(*cp - U'0');
13328 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13329 }
13330 return i;
13331 }
13332
13333 TOML_NODISCARD
13334 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13335 std::string_view parse_basic_string(bool multi_line)
13336 {
13337 return_if_error({});
13338 assert_not_eof();
13339 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'"');
13340 push_parse_scope("string"sv);
13341
13342 // skip the '"'
13343 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13344
13345 // multi-line strings ignore a single line ending right at the beginning
13346 if (multi_line)
13347 {
13348 consume_line_break();
13349 return_if_error({});
13350 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13351 }
13352
13353 auto& str = string_buffer;
13354 str.clear();
13355 bool escaped = false;
13356 bool skipping_whitespace = false;
13357 do
13358 {
13359 if (escaped)
13360 {
13361 escaped = false;
13362
13363 // handle 'line ending slashes' in multi-line mode
13364 if (multi_line && is_whitespace(*cp))
13365 {
13366 consume_leading_whitespace();
13367
13368 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!consume_line_break())
13369 set_error_and_return_default(
13370 "line-ending backslashes must be the last non-whitespace character on the line"sv);
13371
13372 skipping_whitespace = true;
13373 return_if_error({});
13374 continue;
13375 }
13376
13377 bool skip_escaped_codepoint = true;
13378 assert_not_eof();
13379 switch (const auto escaped_codepoint = *cp)
13380 {
13381 // 'regular' escape codes
13382 case U'b': str += '\b'; break;
13383 case U'f': str += '\f'; break;
13384 case U'n': str += '\n'; break;
13385 case U'r': str += '\r'; break;
13386 case U't': str += '\t'; break;
13387 case U'"': str += '"'; break;
13388 case U'\\': str += '\\'; break;
13389
13390#if TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED // toml/pull/790 (\e shorthand for \x1B)
13391 case U'e': str += '\x1B'; break;
13392#else
13393 case U'e':
13394 set_error_and_return_default(
13395 "escape sequence '\\e' is not supported in TOML 1.0.0 and earlier"sv);
13396#endif
13397
13398#if TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED // toml/pull/796 (\xHH unicode scalar sequences)
13399 case U'x': [[fallthrough]];
13400#else
13401 case U'x':
13402 set_error_and_return_default(
13403 "escape sequence '\\x' is not supported in TOML 1.0.0 and earlier"sv);
13404#endif
13405
13406 // unicode scalar sequences
13407 case U'u': [[fallthrough]];
13408 case U'U':
13409 {
13410 push_parse_scope("unicode scalar sequence"sv);
13411 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13412 skip_escaped_codepoint = false;
13413
13414 uint32_t place_value =
13415 escaped_codepoint == U'U' ? 0x10000000u : (escaped_codepoint == U'u' ? 0x1000u : 0x10u);
13416 uint32_t sequence_value{};
13417 while (place_value)
13418 {
13419 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13420
13421 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!is_hexadecimal_digit(*cp))
13422 set_error_and_return_default("expected hex digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13423
13424 sequence_value += place_value * hex_to_dec(*cp);
13425 place_value /= 16u;
13426 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13427 }
13428
13429 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(sequence_value))
13430 set_error_and_return_default(
13431 "unicode surrogates (U+D800 - U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13432 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(sequence_value > 0x10FFFFu)
13433 set_error_and_return_default("values greater than U+10FFFF are invalid"sv);
13434
13435 if (sequence_value < 0x80)
13436 {
13437 str += static_cast<char>(sequence_value);
13438 }
13439 else if (sequence_value < 0x800u)
13440 {
13441 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value >> 6) | 0xC0u);
13442 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13443 }
13444 else if (sequence_value < 0x10000u)
13445 {
13446 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value >> 12) | 0xE0u);
13447 str += static_cast<char>(((sequence_value >> 6) & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13448 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13449 }
13450 else if (sequence_value < 0x110000u)
13451 {
13452 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value >> 18) | 0xF0u);
13453 str += static_cast<char>(((sequence_value >> 12) & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13454 str += static_cast<char>(((sequence_value >> 6) & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13455 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13456 }
13457 break;
13458 }
13459
13460 // ???
13461 TOML_UNLIKELY_CASE
13462 default: set_error_and_return_default("unknown escape sequence '\\"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13463 }
13464
13465 if (skip_escaped_codepoint)
13466 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13467 }
13468 else
13469 {
13470 // handle closing delimiters
13471 if (*cp == U'"')
13472 {
13473 if (multi_line)
13474 {
13475 size_t lookaheads = {};
13476 size_t consecutive_delimiters = 1;
13477 do
13478 {
13479 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13480 lookaheads++;
13481 if (!is_eof() && *cp == U'"')
13482 consecutive_delimiters++;
13483 else
13484 break;
13485 } while (lookaheads < 4u);
13486
13487 switch (consecutive_delimiters)
13488 {
13489 // """ " (one quote somewhere in a ML string)
13490 case 1:
13491 str += '"';
13492 skipping_whitespace = false;
13493 continue;
13494
13495 // """ "" (two quotes somewhere in a ML string)
13496 case 2:
13497 str.append("\"\""sv);
13498 skipping_whitespace = false;
13499 continue;
13500
13501 // """ """ (the end of the string)
13502 case 3: return str;
13503
13504 // """ """" (one at the end of the string)
13505 case 4: str += '"'; return str;
13506
13507 // """ """"" (two quotes at the end of the string)
13508 case 5:
13509 str.append("\"\""sv);
13510 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the last '"'
13511 return str;
13512
13513 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
13514 }
13515 }
13516 else
13517 {
13518 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the closing delimiter
13519 return str;
13520 }
13521 }
13522
13523 // handle escapes
13524 else if (*cp == U'\\')
13525 {
13526 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({}); // skip the '\'
13527 skipping_whitespace = false;
13528 escaped = true;
13529 continue;
13530 }
13531
13532 // handle line endings in multi-line mode
13533 if (multi_line && is_ascii_vertical_whitespace(*cp))
13534 {
13535 consume_line_break();
13536 return_if_error({});
13537 if (!skipping_whitespace)
13538 str += '\n';
13539 continue;
13540 }
13541
13542 // handle control characters
13543 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_nontab_control_character(*cp))
13544 set_error_and_return_default(
13545 "unescaped control characters other than TAB (U+0009) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13546
13547#if TOML_LANG_AT_LEAST(1, 0, 0)
13548
13549 // handle surrogates in strings
13550 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(*cp))
13551 set_error_and_return_default(
13552 "unescaped unicode surrogates (U+D800 to U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13553#endif
13554
13555 if (multi_line)
13556 {
13557 if (!skipping_whitespace || !is_horizontal_whitespace(*cp))
13558 {
13559 skipping_whitespace = false;
13560 str.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13561 }
13562 }
13563 else
13564 str.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13565
13566 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13567 }
13568 } while (!is_eof());
13569
13570 set_error_and_return_default("encountered end-of-file"sv);
13571 }
13572
13573 TOML_NODISCARD
13574 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13575 std::string_view parse_literal_string(bool multi_line)
13576 {
13577 return_if_error({});
13578 assert_not_eof();
13579 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'\'');
13580 push_parse_scope("literal string"sv);
13581
13582 // skip the delimiter
13583 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13584
13585 // multi-line strings ignore a single line ending right at the beginning
13586 if (multi_line)
13587 {
13588 consume_line_break();
13589 return_if_error({});
13590 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13591 }
13592
13593 auto& str = string_buffer;
13594 str.clear();
13595 do
13596 {
13597 return_if_error({});
13598
13599 // handle closing delimiters
13600 if (*cp == U'\'')
13601 {
13602 if (multi_line)
13603 {
13604 size_t lookaheads = {};
13605 size_t consecutive_delimiters = 1;
13606 do
13607 {
13608 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13609 lookaheads++;
13610 if (!is_eof() && *cp == U'\'')
13611 consecutive_delimiters++;
13612 else
13613 break;
13614 } while (lookaheads < 4u);
13615
13616 switch (consecutive_delimiters)
13617 {
13618 // ''' ' (one quote somewhere in a ML string)
13619 case 1: str += '\''; continue;
13620
13621 // ''' '' (two quotes somewhere in a ML string)
13622 case 2: str.append("''"sv); continue;
13623
13624 // ''' ''' (the end of the string)
13625 case 3: return str;
13626
13627 // ''' '''' (one at the end of the string)
13628 case 4: str += '\''; return str;
13629
13630 // ''' ''''' (two quotes at the end of the string)
13631 case 5:
13632 str.append("''"sv);
13633 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the last '
13634 return str;
13635
13636 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
13637 }
13638 }
13639 else
13640 {
13641 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the closing delimiter
13642 return str;
13643 }
13644 }
13645
13646 // handle line endings in multi-line mode
13647 if (multi_line && is_ascii_vertical_whitespace(*cp))
13648 {
13649 consume_line_break();
13650 return_if_error({});
13651 str += '\n';
13652 continue;
13653 }
13654
13655 // handle control characters
13656 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_nontab_control_character(*cp))
13657 set_error_and_return_default(
13658 "control characters other than TAB (U+0009) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13659
13660#if TOML_LANG_AT_LEAST(1, 0, 0)
13661
13662 // handle surrogates in strings
13663 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(*cp))
13664 set_error_and_return_default("unicode surrogates (U+D800 - U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13665#endif
13666
13667 str.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13668 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13669 } while (!is_eof());
13670
13671 set_error_and_return_default("encountered end-of-file"sv);
13672 }
13673
13674 TOML_NODISCARD
13675 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13676 parsed_string parse_string()
13677 {
13678 return_if_error({});
13679 assert_not_eof();
13680 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_string_delimiter(*cp));
13681 push_parse_scope("string"sv);
13682
13683 // get the first three characters to determine the string type
13684 const auto first = cp->value;
13685 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13686 const auto second = cp->value;
13687 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13688 const auto third = cp ? cp->value : U'\0';
13689
13690 // if we were eof at the third character then first and second need to be
13691 // the same string character (otherwise it's an unterminated string)
13692 if (is_eof())
13693 {
13694 if (second == first)
13695 return {};
13696
13697 set_error_and_return_default("encountered end-of-file"sv);
13698 }
13699
13700 // if the first three characters are all the same string delimiter then
13701 // it's a multi-line string.
13702 else if (first == second && first == third)
13703 {
13704 return { first == U'\'' ? parse_literal_string(true) : parse_basic_string(true), true };
13705 }
13706
13707 // otherwise it's just a regular string.
13708 else
13709 {
13710 // step back two characters so that the current
13711 // character is the string delimiter
13712 go_back(2u);
13713
13714 return { first == U'\'' ? parse_literal_string(false) : parse_basic_string(false), false };
13715 }
13716 }
13717
13718 TOML_NODISCARD
13719 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13720 std::string_view parse_bare_key_segment()
13721 {
13722 return_if_error({});
13723 assert_not_eof();
13724 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_bare_key_character(*cp));
13725
13726 string_buffer.clear();
13727
13728 while (!is_eof())
13729 {
13730 if (!is_bare_key_character(*cp))
13731 break;
13732
13733 string_buffer.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13734 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13735 }
13736
13737 return string_buffer;
13738 }
13739
13740 TOML_NODISCARD
13741 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13742 bool parse_boolean()
13743 {
13744 return_if_error({});
13745 assert_not_eof();
13746 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U't', U'f', U'T', U'F'));
13747 push_parse_scope("boolean"sv);
13748
13749 start_recording(true);
13750 auto result = is_match(*cp, U't', U'T');
13751 if (!consume_expected_sequence(result ? U"true"sv : U"false"sv))
13752 set_error_and_return_default("expected '"sv,
13753 to_sv(result),
13754 "', saw '"sv,
13755 to_sv(recording_buffer),
13756 "'"sv);
13757 stop_recording();
13758
13759 if (cp && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13760 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13761
13762 return result;
13763 }
13764
13765 TOML_NODISCARD
13766 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13767 double parse_inf_or_nan()
13768 {
13769 return_if_error({});
13770 assert_not_eof();
13771 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U'i', U'n', U'I', U'N', U'+', U'-'));
13772 push_parse_scope("floating-point"sv);
13773
13774 start_recording(true);
13775 const bool negative = *cp == U'-';
13776 if (negative || *cp == U'+')
13777 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13778
13779 const bool inf = is_match(*cp, U'i', U'I');
13780 if (!consume_expected_sequence(inf ? U"inf"sv : U"nan"sv))
13781 set_error_and_return_default("expected '"sv,
13782 inf ? "inf"sv : "nan"sv,
13783 "', saw '"sv,
13784 to_sv(recording_buffer),
13785 "'"sv);
13786 stop_recording();
13787
13788 if (cp && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13789 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13790
13791 return inf ? (negative ? -std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity() : std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity())
13792 : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
13793 }
13794
13795 TOML_NODISCARD
13796 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13797 double parse_float()
13798 {
13799 return_if_error({});
13800 assert_not_eof();
13801 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-', U'.') || is_decimal_digit(*cp));
13802 push_parse_scope("floating-point"sv);
13803
13804 // sign
13805 const int sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
13806 if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
13807 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13808
13809 // consume value chars
13810 char chars[utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length];
13811 size_t length = {};
13812 const utf8_codepoint* prev = {};
13813 bool seen_decimal = false, seen_exponent = false;
13814 char first_integer_part = '\0';
13815 while (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13816 {
13817 if (*cp == U'_')
13818 {
13819 if (!prev || !is_decimal_digit(*prev))
13820 set_error_and_return_default("underscores may only follow digits"sv);
13821
13822 prev = cp;
13823 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13824 continue;
13825 }
13826 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(prev && *prev == U'_' && !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13827 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
13828 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(length == sizeof(chars))
13829 set_error_and_return_default("exceeds length limit of "sv,
13830 sizeof(chars),
13831 " digits"sv,
13832 (seen_exponent ? ""sv : " (consider using exponent notation)"sv));
13833 else if (*cp == U'.')
13834 {
13835 // .1
13836 // -.1
13837 // +.1 (no integer part)
13838 if (!first_integer_part)
13839 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '.'"sv);
13840
13841 // 1.0e+.10 (exponent cannot have '.')
13842 else if (seen_exponent)
13843 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent decimal digit or sign, saw '.'"sv);
13844
13845 // 1.0.e+.10
13846 // 1..0
13847 // (multiple '.')
13848 else if (seen_decimal)
13849 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit or exponent, saw '.'"sv);
13850
13851 seen_decimal = true;
13852 }
13853 else if (is_match(*cp, U'e', U'E'))
13854 {
13855 if (prev && !is_decimal_digit(*prev))
13856 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13857
13858 // 1.0ee+10 (multiple 'e')
13859 else if (seen_exponent)
13860 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13861
13862 seen_decimal = true; // implied
13863 seen_exponent = true;
13864 }
13865 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
13866 {
13867 // 1.-0 (sign in mantissa)
13868 if (!seen_exponent)
13869 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit or '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13870
13871 // 1.0e1-0 (misplaced exponent sign)
13872 else if (!is_match(*prev, U'e', U'E'))
13873 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13874 }
13875 else if (is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13876 {
13877 if (!seen_decimal)
13878 {
13879 if (!first_integer_part)
13880 first_integer_part = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
13881 else if (first_integer_part == '0')
13882 set_error_and_return_default("leading zeroes are prohibited"sv);
13883 }
13884 }
13885 else
13886 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13887
13888 chars[length++] = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
13889 prev = cp;
13890 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13891 }
13892
13893 // sanity-check ending state
13894 if (prev)
13895 {
13896 if (*prev == U'_')
13897 {
13898 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13899 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
13900 }
13901 else if (is_match(*prev, U'e', U'E', U'+', U'-', U'.'))
13902 {
13903 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13904 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13905 }
13906 }
13907
13908 // convert to double
13909 double result;
13910#if TOML_FLOAT_CHARCONV
13911 {
13912 auto fc_result = std::from_chars(chars, chars + length, result);
13913 switch (fc_result.ec)
13914 {
13915 TOML_LIKELY_CASE
13916 case std::errc{}: // ok
13917 return result * sign;
13918
13919 case std::errc::invalid_argument:
13920 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
13921 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13922 "' could not be interpreted as a value"sv);
13923 break;
13924
13925 case std::errc::result_out_of_range:
13926 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
13927 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13928 "' is not representable in 64 bits"sv);
13929 break;
13930
13931 default: //??
13932 set_error_and_return_default("an unspecified error occurred while trying to interpret '"sv,
13933 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13934 "' as a value"sv);
13935 }
13936 }
13937#else
13938 {
13939 std::stringstream ss;
13940 ss.imbue(std::locale::classic());
13941 ss.write(chars, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
13942 if ((ss >> result))
13943 return result * sign;
13944 else
13945 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
13946 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13947 "' could not be interpreted as a value"sv);
13948 }
13949#endif
13950 }
13951
13952 TOML_NODISCARD
13953 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13954 double parse_hex_float()
13955 {
13956 return_if_error({});
13957 assert_not_eof();
13958 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U'0', U'+', U'-'));
13959 push_parse_scope("hexadecimal floating-point"sv);
13960
13961#if TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED // toml/issues/562 (hexfloats)
13962
13963 // sign
13964 const int sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
13965 if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
13966 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13967
13968 // '0'
13969 if (*cp != U'0')
13970 set_error_and_return_default(" expected '0', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13971 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13972
13973 // 'x' or 'X'
13974 if (!is_match(*cp, U'x', U'X'))
13975 set_error_and_return_default("expected 'x' or 'X', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13976 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13977
13978 // <HEX DIGITS> ([.]<HEX DIGITS>)? [pP] [+-]? <DEC DIGITS>
13979
13980 // consume value fragments
13981 struct fragment
13982 {
13983 char chars[24];
13984 size_t length;
13985 double value;
13986 };
13987 fragment fragments[] = {
13988 {}, // mantissa, whole part
13989 {}, // mantissa, fractional part
13990 {} // exponent
13991 };
13992 fragment* current_fragment = fragments;
13993 const utf8_codepoint* prev = {};
13994 int exponent_sign = 1;
13995 while (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13996 {
13997 if (*cp == U'_')
13998 {
13999 if (!prev || !is_hexadecimal_digit(*prev))
14000 set_error_and_return_default("underscores may only follow digits"sv);
14001
14002 prev = cp;
14003 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14004 continue;
14005 }
14006 else if (prev && *prev == U'_' && !is_hexadecimal_digit(*cp))
14007 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14008 else if (*cp == U'.')
14009 {
14010 // 0x10.0p-.0 (exponent cannot have '.')
14011 if (current_fragment == fragments + 2)
14012 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit or sign, saw '.'"sv);
14013
14014 // 0x10.0.p-0 (multiple '.')
14015 else if (current_fragment == fragments + 1)
14016 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit or exponent, saw '.'"sv);
14017
14018 else
14019 current_fragment++;
14020 }
14021 else if (is_match(*cp, U'p', U'P'))
14022 {
14023 // 0x10.0pp-0 (multiple 'p')
14024 if (current_fragment == fragments + 2)
14025 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit or sign, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14026
14027 // 0x.p-0 (mantissa is just '.')
14028 else if (fragments[0].length == 0u && fragments[1].length == 0u)
14029 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14030
14031 else
14032 current_fragment = fragments + 2;
14033 }
14034 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14035 {
14036 // 0x-10.0p-0 (sign in mantissa)
14037 if (current_fragment != fragments + 2)
14038 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit or '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14039
14040 // 0x10.0p0- (misplaced exponent sign)
14041 else if (!is_match(*prev, U'p', U'P'))
14042 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14043
14044 else
14045 exponent_sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
14046 }
14047 else if (current_fragment < fragments + 2 && !is_hexadecimal_digit(*cp))
14048 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit or '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14049 else if (current_fragment == fragments + 2 && !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14050 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit or sign, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14051 else if (current_fragment->length == sizeof(fragment::chars))
14052 set_error_and_return_default("fragment exceeeds maximum length of "sv,
14053 sizeof(fragment::chars),
14054 " characters"sv);
14055 else
14056 current_fragment->chars[current_fragment->length++] = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
14057
14058 prev = cp;
14059 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14060 }
14061
14062 // sanity-check ending state
14063 if (current_fragment != fragments + 2 || current_fragment->length == 0u)
14064 {
14065 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14066 set_error_and_return_default("missing exponent"sv);
14067 }
14068 else if (prev && *prev == U'_')
14069 {
14070 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14071 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14072 }
14073
14074 // calculate values for the three fragments
14075 for (int fragment_idx = 0; fragment_idx < 3; fragment_idx++)
14076 {
14077 auto& f = fragments[fragment_idx];
14078 const uint32_t base = fragment_idx == 2 ? 10u : 16u;
14079
14080 // left-trim zeroes
14081 const char* c = f.chars;
14082 size_t sig = {};
14083 while (f.length && *c == '0')
14084 {
14085 f.length--;
14086 c++;
14087 sig++;
14088 }
14089 if (!f.length)
14090 continue;
14091
14092 // calculate value
14093 auto place = 1u;
14094 for (size_t i = 0; i < f.length - 1u; i++)
14095 place *= base;
14096 uint32_t val{};
14097 while (place)
14098 {
14099 if (base == 16)
14100 val += place * hex_to_dec(*c);
14101 else
14102 val += place * static_cast<uint32_t>(*c - '0');
14103 if (fragment_idx == 1)
14104 sig++;
14105 c++;
14106 place /= base;
14107 }
14108 f.value = static_cast<double>(val);
14109
14110 // shift the fractional part
14111 if (fragment_idx == 1)
14112 {
14113 while (sig--)
14114 f.value /= base;
14115 }
14116 }
14117
14118 return (fragments[0].value + fragments[1].value) * pow(2.0, fragments[2].value * exponent_sign) * sign;
14119
14120#else // !TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED
14121
14122 set_error_and_return_default("hexadecimal floating-point values are not supported "
14123 "in TOML 1.0.0 and earlier"sv);
14124
14125#endif // !TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED
14126 }
14127
14128 template <uint64_t base>
14129 TOML_NODISCARD
14130 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14131 int64_t parse_integer()
14132 {
14133 return_if_error({});
14134 assert_not_eof();
14135 using traits = parse_integer_traits<base>;
14136 push_parse_scope(traits::scope_qualifier);
14137
14138 [[maybe_unused]] int64_t sign = 1;
14139 if constexpr (traits::is_signed)
14140 {
14141 sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
14142 if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14143 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14144 }
14145
14146 if constexpr (base == 10)
14147 {
14148 if (!traits::is_digit(*cp))
14149 set_error_and_return_default("expected expected digit or sign, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14150 }
14151 else
14152 {
14153 // '0'
14154 if (*cp != U'0')
14155 set_error_and_return_default("expected '0', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14156 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14157
14158 // 'b', 'o', 'x'
14159 if (*cp != traits::prefix_codepoint)
14160 set_error_and_return_default("expected '"sv, traits::prefix, "', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14161 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14162
14163 if (!traits::is_digit(*cp))
14164 set_error_and_return_default("expected digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14165 }
14166
14167 // consume digits
14168 char digits[utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length];
14169 size_t length = {};
14170 const utf8_codepoint* prev = {};
14171 while (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14172 {
14173 if (*cp == U'_')
14174 {
14175 if (!prev || !traits::is_digit(*prev))
14176 set_error_and_return_default("underscores may only follow digits"sv);
14177
14178 prev = cp;
14179 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14180 continue;
14181 }
14182 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(prev && *prev == U'_' && !traits::is_digit(*cp))
14183 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14184 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(!traits::is_digit(*cp))
14185 set_error_and_return_default("expected digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14186 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(length == sizeof(digits))
14187 set_error_and_return_default("exceeds length limit of "sv, sizeof(digits), " digits"sv);
14188 else
14189 digits[length++] = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
14190
14191 prev = cp;
14192 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14193 }
14194
14195 // sanity check ending state
14196 if (prev && *prev == U'_')
14197 {
14198 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14199 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14200 }
14201
14202 // single digits can be converted trivially
14203 if (length == 1u)
14204 {
14205 int64_t result;
14206
14207 if constexpr (base == 16)
14208 result = static_cast<int64_t>(hex_to_dec(digits[0]));
14209 else
14210 result = static_cast<int64_t>(digits[0] - '0');
14211
14212 if constexpr (traits::is_signed)
14213 result *= sign;
14214
14215 return result;
14216 }
14217
14218 // bin, oct and hex allow leading zeroes so trim them first
14219 const char* end = digits + length;
14220 const char* msd = digits;
14221 if constexpr (base != 10)
14222 {
14223 while (msd < end && *msd == '0')
14224 msd++;
14225 if (msd == end)
14226 return 0ll;
14227 }
14228
14229 // decimal integers do not allow leading zeroes
14230 else
14231 {
14232 if TOML_UNLIKELY(digits[0] == '0')
14233 set_error_and_return_default("leading zeroes are prohibited"sv);
14234 }
14235
14236 // range check
14237 if TOML_UNLIKELY(static_cast<size_t>(end - msd) > traits::max_digits)
14238 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
14239 traits::full_prefix,
14240 std::string_view{ digits, length },
14241 "' is not representable in 64 bits"sv);
14242
14243 // do the thing
14244 {
14245 uint64_t result = {};
14246 {
14247 uint64_t power = 1;
14248 while (--end >= msd)
14249 {
14250 if constexpr (base == 16)
14251 result += power * hex_to_dec(*end);
14252 else
14253 result += power * static_cast<uint64_t>(*end - '0');
14254
14255 power *= base;
14256 }
14257 }
14258
14259 // range check
14260 static constexpr auto i64_max = static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)());
14261 if TOML_UNLIKELY(result > i64_max + (sign < 0 ? 1u : 0u))
14262 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
14263 traits::full_prefix,
14264 std::string_view{ digits, length },
14265 "' is not representable in 64 bits"sv);
14266
14267 if constexpr (traits::is_signed)
14268 {
14269 // avoid signed multiply UB when parsing INT64_MIN
14270 if TOML_UNLIKELY(sign < 0 && result == i64_max + 1u)
14271 return (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)();
14272
14273 return static_cast<int64_t>(result) * sign;
14274 }
14275 else
14276 return static_cast<int64_t>(result);
14277 }
14278 }
14279
14280 TOML_NODISCARD
14281 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14282 date parse_date(bool part_of_datetime = false)
14283 {
14284 return_if_error({});
14285 assert_not_eof();
14286 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_decimal_digit(*cp));
14287 push_parse_scope("date"sv);
14288
14289 // "YYYY"
14290 uint32_t digits[4];
14291 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 4u))
14292 set_error_and_return_default("expected 4-digit year, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14293 const auto year = digits[3] + digits[2] * 10u + digits[1] * 100u + digits[0] * 1000u;
14294 const auto is_leap_year = (year % 4u == 0u) && ((year % 100u != 0u) || (year % 400u == 0u));
14295 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14296
14297 // '-'
14298 if (*cp != U'-')
14299 set_error_and_return_default("expected '-', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14300 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14301
14302 // "MM"
14303 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14304 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit month, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14305 const auto month = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14306 if (month == 0u || month > 12u)
14307 set_error_and_return_default("expected month between 1 and 12 (inclusive), saw "sv, month);
14308 const auto max_days_in_month = month == 2u
14309 ? (is_leap_year ? 29u : 28u)
14310 : (month == 4u || month == 6u || month == 9u || month == 11u ? 30u : 31u);
14311 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14312
14313 // '-'
14314 if (*cp != U'-')
14315 set_error_and_return_default("expected '-', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14316 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14317
14318 // "DD"
14319 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14320 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit day, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14321 const auto day = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14322 if (day == 0u || day > max_days_in_month)
14323 set_error_and_return_default("expected day between 1 and "sv,
14324 max_days_in_month,
14325 " (inclusive), saw "sv,
14326 day);
14327
14328 if (!part_of_datetime && !is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14329 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14330
14331 return { year, month, day };
14332 }
14333
14334 TOML_NODISCARD
14335 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14336 time parse_time(bool part_of_datetime = false)
14337 {
14338 return_if_error({});
14339 assert_not_eof();
14340 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_decimal_digit(*cp));
14341 push_parse_scope("time"sv);
14342
14343 static constexpr size_t max_digits = 64; // far more than necessary but needed to allow fractional
14344 // millisecond truncation per the spec
14345uint32_t digits[max_digits];
14346
14347// "HH"
14348if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14349 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit hour, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14350const auto hour = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14351if (hour > 23u)
14352 set_error_and_return_default("expected hour between 0 to 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, hour);
14353set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14354
14355// ':'
14356if (*cp != U':')
14357 set_error_and_return_default("expected ':', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14358advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14359
14360// "MM"
14361if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14362 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit minute, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14363const auto minute = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14364if (minute > 59u)
14365 set_error_and_return_default("expected minute between 0 and 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, minute);
14366auto time = toml::time{ hour, minute };
14367
14368// ':'
14369if constexpr (TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED) // toml/issues/671 (allow omission of seconds)
14370{
14371 if (is_eof() || is_value_terminator(*cp) || (part_of_datetime && is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-', U'Z', U'z')))
14372 return time;
14373}
14374else
14375 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14376if (*cp != U':')
14377 set_error_and_return_default("expected ':', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14378advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14379
14380// "SS"
14381if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14382 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit second, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14383const auto second = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14384if (second > 59u)
14385 set_error_and_return_default("expected second between 0 and 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, second);
14386time.second = static_cast<decltype(time.second)>(second);
14387
14388// '.' (early-exiting is allowed; fractional is optional)
14389if (is_eof() || is_value_terminator(*cp) || (part_of_datetime && is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-', U'Z', U'z')))
14390 return time;
14391if (*cp != U'.')
14392 set_error_and_return_default("expected '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14393advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14394
14395// "FFFFFFFFF"
14396size_t digit_count = consume_variable_length_digit_sequence(digits, max_digits);
14397if (!digit_count)
14398{
14399 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14400 set_error_and_return_default("expected fractional digits, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14401}
14402else if (!is_eof())
14403{
14404 if (digit_count == max_digits && is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14405 set_error_and_return_default("fractional component exceeds maximum precision of "sv, max_digits);
14406 else if (!part_of_datetime && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14407 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14408}
14409uint32_t value = 0u;
14410uint32_t place = 1u;
14411for (auto i = impl::min<size_t>(digit_count, 9u); i-- > 0u;)
14412{
14413 value += digits[i] * place;
14414 place *= 10u;
14415}
14416for (auto i = digit_count; i < 9u; i++) // implicit zeros
14417 value *= 10u;
14418time.nanosecond = value;
14419return time;
14420}
14421
14422TOML_NODISCARD
14423TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14424date_time parse_date_time()
14425{
14426 return_if_error({});
14427 assert_not_eof();
14428 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_decimal_digit(*cp));
14429 push_parse_scope("date-time"sv);
14430
14431 // "YYYY-MM-DD"
14432 auto date = parse_date(true);
14433 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14434
14435 // ' ', 'T' or 't'
14436 if (!is_match(*cp, U' ', U'T', U't'))
14437 set_error_and_return_default("expected space, 'T' or 't', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14438 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14439
14440 // "HH:MM:SS.FFFFFFFFF"
14441 auto time = parse_time(true);
14442 return_if_error({});
14443
14444 // no offset
14445 if (is_eof() || is_value_terminator(*cp))
14446 return { date, time };
14447
14448 // zero offset ('Z' or 'z')
14449 time_offset offset{};
14450 if (is_match(*cp, U'Z', U'z'))
14451 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14452
14453 // explicit offset ("+/-HH:MM")
14454 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14455 {
14456 push_parse_scope("date-time offset"sv);
14457
14458 // sign
14459 int sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
14460 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14461
14462 // "HH"
14463 int digits[2];
14464 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14465 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit hour, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14466 const auto hour = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10;
14467 if (hour > 23)
14468 set_error_and_return_default("expected hour between 0 and 23 (inclusive), saw "sv, hour);
14469 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14470
14471 // ':'
14472 if (*cp != U':')
14473 set_error_and_return_default("expected ':', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14474 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14475
14476 // "MM"
14477 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14478 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit minute, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14479 const auto minute = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10;
14480 if (minute > 59)
14481 set_error_and_return_default("expected minute between 0 and 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, minute);
14482 offset.minutes = static_cast<decltype(offset.minutes)>((hour * 60 + minute) * sign);
14483 }
14484
14485 if (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14486 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14487
14488 return { date, time, offset };
14489}
14490
14491TOML_NODISCARD
14492node_ptr parse_array();
14493
14494TOML_NODISCARD
14495node_ptr parse_inline_table();
14496
14497TOML_NODISCARD
14498node_ptr parse_value_known_prefixes()
14499{
14500 return_if_error({});
14501 assert_not_eof();
14502 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_control_character(*cp));
14503 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp != U'_');
14504
14505 switch (cp->value)
14506 {
14507 // arrays
14508 case U'[': return parse_array();
14509
