14510 // inline tables
14511 case U'{': return parse_inline_table();
14512
14513 // floats beginning with '.'
14514 case U'.': return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_float() } };
14515
14516 // strings
14517 case U'"': [[fallthrough]];
14518 case U'\'': return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_string().value } };
14519
14520 default:
14521 {
14522 const auto cp_upper = static_cast<uint_least32_t>(cp->value) & ~0x20u;
14523
14524 // bools
14525 if (cp_upper == 70u || cp_upper == 84u) // F or T
14526 return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_boolean() } };
14527
14528 // inf/nan
14529 else if (cp_upper == 73u || cp_upper == 78u) // I or N
14530 return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_inf_or_nan() } };
14531
14532 else
14533 return nullptr;
14534 }
14535 }
14536 TOML_UNREACHABLE;
14537 }
14538
14539 TOML_NODISCARD
14540 node_ptr parse_value()
14541 {
14542 return_if_error({});
14543 assert_not_eof();
14544 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_value_terminator(*cp));
14545 push_parse_scope("value"sv);
14546
14547 const depth_counter_scope depth_counter{ nested_values };
14548 if TOML_UNLIKELY(nested_values > max_nested_values)
14549 set_error_and_return_default("exceeded maximum nested value depth of "sv,
14550 max_nested_values,
14551 " (TOML_MAX_NESTED_VALUES)"sv);
14552
14553 // check if it begins with some control character
14554 // (note that this will also fail for whitespace but we're assuming we've
14555 // called consume_leading_whitespace() before calling parse_value())
14556 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_control_character(*cp))
14557 set_error_and_return_default("unexpected control character"sv);
14558
14559 // underscores at the beginning
14560 else if (*cp == U'_')
14561 set_error_and_return_default("values may not begin with underscores"sv);
14562
14563 const auto begin_pos = cp->position;
14564 node_ptr val;
14565
14566 do
14567 {
14568 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_control_character(*cp));
14569 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp != U'_');
14570
14571 // detect the value type and parse accordingly,
14572 // starting with value types that can be detected
14573 // unambiguously from just one character.
14574
14575 val = parse_value_known_prefixes();
14576 return_if_error({});
14577 if (val)
14578 break;
14579
14580 // value types from here down require more than one character to unambiguously identify
14581 // so scan ahead and collect a set of value 'traits'.
14582 enum TOML_CLOSED_FLAGS_ENUM value_traits : int
14583 {
14584 has_nothing = 0,
14585 has_digits = 1,
14586 has_b = 1 << 1, // as second char only (0b)
14587 has_e = 1 << 2, // only float exponents
14588 has_o = 1 << 3, // as second char only (0o)
14589 has_p = 1 << 4, // only hexfloat exponents
14590 has_t = 1 << 5,
14591 has_x = 1 << 6, // as second or third char only (0x, -0x, +0x)
14592 has_z = 1 << 7,
14593 has_colon = 1 << 8,
14594 has_plus = 1 << 9,
14595 has_minus = 1 << 10,
14596 has_dot = 1 << 11,
14597 begins_sign = 1 << 12,
14598 begins_digit = 1 << 13,
14599 begins_zero = 1 << 14,
14600 signs_msk = has_plus | has_minus,
14601 bdigit_msk = has_digits | begins_digit,
14602 bzero_msk = bdigit_msk | begins_zero,
14603 };
14604 value_traits traits = has_nothing;
14605 const auto has_any = [&](auto t) noexcept { return (traits & t) != has_nothing; };
14606 const auto has_none = [&](auto t) noexcept { return (traits & t) == has_nothing; };
14607 const auto add_trait = [&](auto t) noexcept { traits = static_cast<value_traits>(traits | t); };
14608
14609 // examine the first character to get the 'begins with' traits
14610 // (good fail-fast opportunity; all the remaining types begin with numeric digits or signs)
14611 if (is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14612 {
14613 add_trait(begins_digit);
14614 if (*cp == U'0')
14615 add_trait(begins_zero);
14616 }
14617 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14618 add_trait(begins_sign);
14619 else
14620 break;
14621
14622 // scan the rest of the value to determine the remaining traits
14623 char32_t chars[utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length];
14624 size_t char_count = {}, advance_count = {};
14625 bool eof_while_scanning = false;
14626 const auto scan = [&]() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
14627 {
14628 if (is_eof())
14629 return;
14630 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_value_terminator(*cp));
14631
14632 do
14633 {
14634 if (const auto c = **cp; c != U'_')
14635 {
14636 chars[char_count++] = c;
14637
14638 if (is_decimal_digit(c))
14639 add_trait(has_digits);
14640 else if (is_ascii_letter(c))
14641 {
14642 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME((c >= U'a' && c <= U'z') || (c >= U'A' && c <= U'Z'));
14643 switch (static_cast<char32_t>(c | 32u))
14644 {
14645 case U'b':
14646 if (char_count == 2u && has_any(begins_zero))
14647 add_trait(has_b);
14648 break;
14649
14650 case U'e':
14651 if (char_count > 1u
14652 && has_none(has_b | has_o | has_p | has_t | has_x | has_z | has_colon)
14653 && (has_none(has_plus | has_minus) || has_any(begins_sign)))
14654 add_trait(has_e);
14655 break;
14656
14657 case U'o':
14658 if (char_count == 2u && has_any(begins_zero))
14659 add_trait(has_o);
14660 break;
14661
14662 case U'p':
14663 if (has_any(has_x))
14664 add_trait(has_p);
14665 break;
14666
14667 case U'x':
14668 if ((char_count == 2u && has_any(begins_zero))
14669 || (char_count == 3u && has_any(begins_sign) && chars[1] == U'0'))
14670 add_trait(has_x);
14671 break;
14672
14673 case U't': add_trait(has_t); break;
14674 case U'z': add_trait(has_z); break;
14675 }
14676 }
14677 else if (c <= U':')
14678 {
14679 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(c < U'0' || c > U'9');
14680 switch (c)
14681 {
14682 case U'+': add_trait(has_plus); break;
14683 case U'-': add_trait(has_minus); break;
14684 case U'.': add_trait(has_dot); break;
14685 case U':': add_trait(has_colon); break;
14686 }
14687 }
14688 }
14689
14690 advance_and_return_if_error();
14691 advance_count++;
14692 eof_while_scanning = is_eof();
14693 } while (advance_count < (utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length - 1u) && !is_eof()
14694 && !is_value_terminator(*cp));
14695 };
14696 scan();
14697 return_if_error({});
14698
14699 // force further scanning if this could have been a date-time with a space instead of a T
14700 if (char_count == 10u //
14701 && (traits | begins_zero) == (bzero_msk | has_minus) //
14702 && chars[4] == U'-' //
14703 && chars[7] == U'-' //
14704 && !is_eof() //
14705 && *cp == U' ')
14706 {
14707 const auto pre_advance_count = advance_count;
14708 const auto pre_scan_traits = traits;
14709 chars[char_count++] = *cp;
14710 add_trait(has_t);
14711
14712 const auto backpedal = [&]() noexcept
14713 {
14714 go_back(advance_count - pre_advance_count);
14715 advance_count = pre_advance_count;
14716 traits = pre_scan_traits;
14717 char_count = 10u;
14718 };
14719
14720 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14721 advance_count++;
14722
14723 if (is_eof() || !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14724 backpedal();
14725 else
14726 {
14727 chars[char_count++] = *cp;
14728
14729 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14730 advance_count++;
14731
14732 scan();
14733 return_if_error({});
14734
14735 if (char_count == 12u)
14736 backpedal();
14737 }
14738 }
14739
14740 // set the reader back to where we started
14741 go_back(advance_count);
14742
14743 // if after scanning ahead we still only have one value character,
14744 // the only valid value type is an integer.
14745 if (char_count == 1u)
14746 {
14747 if (has_any(begins_digit))
14748 {
14749 val.reset(new value{ static_cast<int64_t>(chars[0] - U'0') });
14750 advance(); // skip the digit
14751 break;
14752 }
14753
14754 // anything else would be ambiguous.
14755 else
14756 set_error_and_return_default(eof_while_scanning ? "encountered end-of-file"sv
14757 : "could not determine value type"sv);
14758 }
14759
14760 // now things that can be identified from two or more characters
14761 return_if_error({});
14762 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(char_count >= 2u);
14763
14764 // do some 'fuzzy matching' where there's no ambiguity, since that allows the specific
14765 // typed parse functions to take over and show better diagnostics if there's an issue
14766 // (as opposed to the fallback "could not determine type" message)
14767 if (has_any(has_p))
14768 val.reset(new value{ parse_hex_float() });
14769 else if (has_any(has_x | has_o | has_b))
14770 {
14771 int64_t i;
14772 value_flags flags;
14773 if (has_any(has_x))
14774 {
14775 i = parse_integer<16>();
14776 flags = value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal;
14777 }
14778 else if (has_any(has_o))
14779 {
14780 i = parse_integer<8>();
14781 flags = value_flags::format_as_octal;
14782 }
14783 else // has_b
14784 {
14785 i = parse_integer<2>();
14786 flags = value_flags::format_as_binary;
14787 }
14788 return_if_error({});
14789
14790 val.reset(new value{ i });
14791 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(flags);
14792 }
14793 else if (has_any(has_e) || (has_any(begins_digit) && chars[1] == U'.'))
14794 val.reset(new value{ parse_float() });
14795 else if (has_any(begins_sign))
14796 {
14797 // single-digit signed integers
14798 if (char_count == 2u && has_any(has_digits))
14799 {
14800 val.reset(new value{ static_cast<int64_t>(chars[1] - U'0') * (chars[0] == U'-' ? -1LL : 1LL) });
14801 advance(); // skip the sign
14802 advance(); // skip the digit
14803 break;
14804 }
14805
14806 // simple signed floats (e.g. +1.0)
14807 if (is_decimal_digit(chars[1]) && chars[2] == U'.')
14808 val.reset(new value{ parse_float() });
14809
14810 // signed infinity or nan
14811 else if (is_match(chars[1], U'i', U'n', U'I', U'N'))
14812 val.reset(new value{ parse_inf_or_nan() });
14813 }
14814
14815 return_if_error({});
14816 if (val)
14817 break;
14818
14819 // match trait masks against what they can match exclusively.
14820 // all correct value parses will come out of this list, so doing this as a switch is likely to
14821 // be a better friend to the optimizer on the success path (failure path can be slow but that
14822 // doesn't matter much).
14823 switch (unwrap_enum(traits))
14824 {
14825 // binary integers
14826 // 0b10
14827 case bzero_msk | has_b:
14828 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<2>() });
14829 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(value_flags::format_as_binary);
14830 break;
14831
14832 // octal integers
14833 // 0o10
14834 case bzero_msk | has_o:
14835 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<8>() });
14836 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(value_flags::format_as_octal);
14837 break;
14838
14839 // decimal integers
14840 // 00
14841 // 10
14842 // +10
14843 // -10
14844 case bzero_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14845 case bdigit_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14846 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14847 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_plus:
14848 {
14849 // if the value was so long we exhausted the history buffer it's reasonable to assume
14850 // there was more and the value's actual type is impossible to identify without making the
14851 // buffer bigger (since it could have actually been a float), so emit an error.
14852 //
14853 // (this will likely only come up during fuzzing and similar scenarios)
14854 static constexpr size_t max_numeric_value_length =
14855 utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length - 2u;
14856 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!eof_while_scanning && advance_count > max_numeric_value_length)
14857 set_error_and_return_default("numeric value too long to identify type - cannot exceed "sv,
14858 max_numeric_value_length,
14859 " characters"sv);
14860
14861 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<10>() });
14862 break;
14863 }
14864
14865 // hexadecimal integers
14866 // 0x10
14867 case bzero_msk | has_x:
14868 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<16>() });
14869 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal);
14870 break;
14871
14872 // decimal floats
14873 // 0e1
14874 // 0e-1
14875 // 0e+1
14876 // 0.0
14877 // 0.0e1
14878 // 0.0e-1
14879 // 0.0e+1
14880 case bzero_msk | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14881 case bzero_msk | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14882 case bzero_msk | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14883 case bzero_msk | has_dot: [[fallthrough]];
14884 case bzero_msk | has_dot | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14885 case bzero_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14886 case bzero_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14887 // 1e1
14888 // 1e-1
14889 // 1e+1
14890 // 1.0
14891 // 1.0e1
14892 // 1.0e-1
14893 // 1.0e+1
14894 case bdigit_msk | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14895 case bdigit_msk | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14896 case bdigit_msk | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14897 case bdigit_msk | has_dot: [[fallthrough]];
14898 case bdigit_msk | has_dot | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14899 case bdigit_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14900 case bdigit_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14901 // +1e1
14902 // +1.0
14903 // +1.0e1
14904 // +1.0e+1
14905 // +1.0e-1
14906 // -1.0e+1
14907 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14908 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14909 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14910 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_e | signs_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14911 // -1e1
14912 // -1e+1
14913 // +1e-1
14914 // -1.0
14915 // -1.0e1
14916 // -1.0e-1
14917 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14918 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_e | signs_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14919 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14920 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_e | has_minus:
14921 val.reset(new value{ parse_float() });
14922 break;
14923
14924 // hexadecimal floats
14925 // 0x10p0
14926 // 0x10p-0
14927 // 0x10p+0
14928 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_p: [[fallthrough]];
14929 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14930 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14931 // -0x10p0
14932 // -0x10p-0
14933 // +0x10p0
14934 // +0x10p+0
14935 // -0x10p+0
14936 // +0x10p-0
14937 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14938 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14939 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_p | signs_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14940 // 0x10.1p0
14941 // 0x10.1p-0
14942 // 0x10.1p+0
14943 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_dot | has_p: [[fallthrough]];
14944 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14945 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14946 // -0x10.1p0
14947 // -0x10.1p-0
14948 // +0x10.1p0
14949 // +0x10.1p+0
14950 // -0x10.1p+0
14951 // +0x10.1p-0
14952 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14953 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14954 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_dot | has_p | signs_msk:
14955 val.reset(new value{ parse_hex_float() });
14956 break;
14957
14958 // times
14959 // HH:MM
14960 // HH:MM:SS
14961 // HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF
14962 case bzero_msk | has_colon: [[fallthrough]];
14963 case bzero_msk | has_colon | has_dot: [[fallthrough]];
14964 case bdigit_msk | has_colon: [[fallthrough]];
14965 case bdigit_msk | has_colon | has_dot: val.reset(new value{ parse_time() }); break;
14966
14967 // local dates
14968 // YYYY-MM-DD
14969 case bzero_msk | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14970 case bdigit_msk | has_minus: val.reset(new value{ parse_date() }); break;
14971
14972 // date-times
14973 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM
14974 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM-HH:MM
14975 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM+HH:MM
14976 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM
14977 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM-HH:MM
14978 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM+HH:MM
14979 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS
14980 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS-HH:MM
14981 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+HH:MM
14982 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
14983 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS-HH:MM
14984 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS+HH:MM
14985 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14986 case bzero_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14987 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14988 case bdigit_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14989 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFF
14990 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFF-HH:MM
14991 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFF+HH:MM
14992 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF
14993 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF-HH:MM
14994 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF+HH:MM
14995 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14996 case bzero_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14997 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14998 case bdigit_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14999 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MMZ
15000 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MMZ
15001 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ
15002 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SSZ
15003 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFFZ
15004 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFFZ
15005 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_z | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15006 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_z | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15007 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_z | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15008 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_z | has_t:
15009 val.reset(new value{ parse_date_time() });
15010 break;
15011 }
15012 } while (false);
15013
15014 if (!val)
15015 {
15016 set_error_at(begin_pos, "could not determine value type"sv);
15017 return_after_error({});
15018 }
15019
15020 val->source_ = { begin_pos, current_position(1), reader.source_path() };
15021 return val;
15022 }
15023
15024 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
15025 bool parse_key()
15026 {
15027 return_if_error({});
15028 assert_not_eof();
15029 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_bare_key_character(*cp) || is_string_delimiter(*cp));
15030 push_parse_scope("key"sv);
15031
15032 key_buffer.clear();
15033 recording_whitespace = false;
15034
15035 while (!is_error())
15036 {
15037 std::string_view key_segment;
15038 const auto key_begin = current_position();
15039
15040 // bare_key_segment
15041 if (is_bare_key_character(*cp))
15042 key_segment = parse_bare_key_segment();
15043
15044 // "quoted key segment"
15045 else if (is_string_delimiter(*cp))
15046 {
15047 const auto begin_pos = cp->position;
15048
15049 recording_whitespace = true;
15050 parsed_string str = parse_string();
15051 recording_whitespace = false;
15052 return_if_error({});
15053
15054 if (str.was_multi_line)
15055 {
15056 set_error_at(begin_pos,
15057 "multi-line strings are prohibited in "sv,
15058 key_buffer.empty() ? ""sv : "dotted "sv,
15059 "keys"sv);
15060 return_after_error({});
15061 }
15062 else
15063 key_segment = str.value;
15064 }
15065
15066 // ???
15067 else
15068 set_error_and_return_default("expected bare key starting character or string delimiter, saw '"sv,
15069 to_sv(*cp),
15070 "'"sv);
15071
15072 const auto key_end = current_position();
15073
15074 // whitespace following the key segment
15075 consume_leading_whitespace();
15076
15077 // store segment
15078 key_buffer.push_back(key_segment, key_begin, key_end);
15079
15080 // eof or no more key to come
15081 if (is_eof() || *cp != U'.')
15082 break;
15083
15084 // was a dotted key - go around again
15085 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15086 consume_leading_whitespace();
15087 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15088 }
15089 return_if_error({});
15090
15091 return true;
15092 }
15093
15094 TOML_NODISCARD
15095 key make_key(size_t segment_index) const
15096 {
15097 TOML_ASSERT(key_buffer.size() > segment_index);
15098
15099 return key{
15100 key_buffer[segment_index],
15101 source_region{ key_buffer.starts[segment_index], key_buffer.ends[segment_index], root.source().path }
15102 };
15103 }
15104
15105 TOML_NODISCARD
15106 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
15107 table* parse_table_header()
15108 {
15109 return_if_error({});
15110 assert_not_eof();
15111 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'[');
15112 push_parse_scope("table header"sv);
15113
15114 const source_position header_begin_pos = cp->position;
15115 source_position header_end_pos;
15116 bool is_arr = false;
15117
15118 // parse header
15119 {
15120 // skip first '['
15121 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15122
15123 // skip past any whitespace that followed the '['
15124 const bool had_leading_whitespace = consume_leading_whitespace();
15125 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15126
15127 // skip second '[' (if present)
15128 if (*cp == U'[')
15129 {
15130 if (had_leading_whitespace)
15131 set_error_and_return_default(
15132 "[[array-of-table]] brackets must be contiguous (i.e. [ [ this ] ] is prohibited)"sv);
15133
15134 is_arr = true;
15135 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15136
15137 // skip past any whitespace that followed the '['
15138 consume_leading_whitespace();
15139 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15140 }
15141
15142 // check for a premature closing ']'
15143 if (*cp == U']')
15144 set_error_and_return_default("tables with blank bare keys are explicitly prohibited"sv);
15145
15146 // get the actual key
15147 start_recording();
15148 parse_key();
15149 stop_recording(1u);
15150 return_if_error({});
15151
15152 // skip past any whitespace that followed the key
15153 consume_leading_whitespace();
15154 return_if_error({});
15155 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15156
15157 // consume the closing ']'
15158 if (*cp != U']')
15159 set_error_and_return_default("expected ']', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15160 if (is_arr)
15161 {
15162 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15163 if (*cp != U']')
15164 set_error_and_return_default("expected ']', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15165 }
15166 advance_and_return_if_error({});
15167 header_end_pos = current_position(1);
15168
15169 // handle the rest of the line after the header
15170 consume_leading_whitespace();
15171 if (!is_eof() && !consume_comment() && !consume_line_break())
15172 set_error_and_return_default("expected a comment or whitespace, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
15173 }
15174 TOML_ASSERT(!key_buffer.empty());
15175
15176 // check if each parent is a table/table array, or can be created implicitly as a table.
15177 table* parent = &root;
15178 for (size_t i = 0, e = key_buffer.size() - 1u; i < e; i++)
15179 {
15180 const std::string_view segment = key_buffer[i];
15181 auto pit = parent->lower_bound(segment);
15182
15183 // parent already existed
15184 if (pit != parent->end() && pit->first == segment)
15185 {
15186 node& p = pit->second;
15187
15188 if (auto tbl = p.as_table())
15189 {
15190 // adding to closed inline tables is illegal
15191 if (tbl->is_inline() && !impl::find(open_inline_tables.begin(), open_inline_tables.end(), tbl))
15192 set_error_and_return_default("cannot insert '"sv,
15193 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15194 "' into existing inline table"sv);
15195
15196 parent = tbl;
15197 }
15198 else if (auto arr = p.as_array(); arr && impl::find(table_arrays.begin(), table_arrays.end(), arr))
15199 {
15200 // table arrays are a special case;
15201 // the spec dictates we select the most recently declared element in the array.
15202 TOML_ASSERT(!arr->empty());
15203 TOML_ASSERT(arr->back().is_table());
15204 parent = &arr->back().ref_cast<table>();
15205 }
15206 else
15207 {
15208 if (!is_arr && p.type() == node_type::table)
15209 set_error_and_return_default("cannot redefine existing table '"sv,
15210 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15211 "'"sv);
15212 else
15213 set_error_and_return_default("cannot redefine existing "sv,
15214 to_sv(p.type()),
15215 " '"sv,
15216 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15217 "' as "sv,
15218 is_arr ? "array-of-tables"sv : "table"sv);
15219 }
15220 }
15221
15222 // need to create a new implicit table
15223 else
15224 {
15225 pit = parent->emplace_hint<table>(pit, make_key(i));
15226 table& p = pit->second.ref_cast<table>();
15227 p.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15228
15229 implicit_tables.push_back(&p);
15230 parent = &p;
15231 }
15232 }
15233
15234 const auto last_segment = key_buffer.back();
15235 auto it = parent->lower_bound(last_segment);
15236
15237 // if there was already a matching node some sanity checking is necessary;
15238 // this is ok if we're making an array and the existing element is already an array (new element)
15239 // or if we're making a table and the existing element is an implicitly-created table (promote it),
15240 // otherwise this is a redefinition error.
15241 if (it != parent->end() && it->first == last_segment)
15242 {
15243 node& matching_node = it->second;
15244 if (auto arr = matching_node.as_array();
15245 is_arr && arr && impl::find(table_arrays.begin(), table_arrays.end(), arr))
15246 {
15247 table& tbl = arr->emplace_back<table>();
15248 tbl.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15249 return &tbl;
15250 }
15251
15252 else if (auto tbl = matching_node.as_table(); !is_arr && tbl && !implicit_tables.empty())
15253 {
15254 if (auto found = impl::find(implicit_tables.begin(), implicit_tables.end(), tbl); found)
15255 {
15256 bool ok = true;
15257 if (!tbl->empty())
15258 {
15259 for (auto& [_, child] : *tbl)
15260 {
15261 if (!child.is_table() && !child.is_array_of_tables())
15262 {
15263 ok = false;
15264 break;
15265 }
15266 }
15267 }
15268
15269 if (ok)
15270 {
15271 implicit_tables.erase(implicit_tables.cbegin() + (found - implicit_tables.data()));
15272 tbl->source_.begin = header_begin_pos;
15273 tbl->source_.end = header_end_pos;
15274 return tbl;
15275 }
15276 }
15277 }
15278
15279 // if we get here it's a redefinition error.
15280 if (!is_arr && matching_node.type() == node_type::table)
15281 {
15282 set_error_at(header_begin_pos,
15283 "cannot redefine existing table '"sv,
15284 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15285 "'"sv);
15286 return_after_error({});
15287 }
15288 else
15289 {
15290 set_error_at(header_begin_pos,
15291 "cannot redefine existing "sv,
15292 to_sv(matching_node.type()),
15293 " '"sv,
15294 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15295 "' as "sv,
15296 is_arr ? "array-of-tables"sv : "table"sv);
15297 return_after_error({});
15298 }
15299 }
15300
15301 // there was no matching node, sweet - we can freely instantiate a new table/table array.
15302 else
15303 {
15304 auto last_key = make_key(key_buffer.size() - 1u);
15305
15306 // if it's an array we need to make the array and it's first table element,
15307 // set the starting regions, and return the table element
15308 if (is_arr)
15309 {
15310 it = parent->emplace_hint<array>(it, std::move(last_key));
15311 array& tbl_arr = it->second.ref_cast<array>();
15312 table_arrays.push_back(&tbl_arr);
15313 tbl_arr.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15314
15315 table& tbl = tbl_arr.emplace_back<table>();
15316 tbl.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15317 return &tbl;
15318 }
15319
15320 // otherwise we're just making a table
15321 else
15322 {
15323 it = parent->emplace_hint<table>(it, std::move(last_key));
15324 table& tbl = it->second.ref_cast<table>();
15325 tbl.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15326 return &tbl;
15327 }
15328 }
15329 }
15330
15331 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
15332 bool parse_key_value_pair_and_insert(table* tbl)
15333 {
15334 return_if_error({});
15335 assert_not_eof();
15336 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_string_delimiter(*cp) || is_bare_key_character(*cp));
15337 push_parse_scope("key-value pair"sv);
15338
15339 // read the key into the key buffer
15340 start_recording();
15341 parse_key();
15342 stop_recording(1u);
15343 return_if_error({});
15344 TOML_ASSERT(key_buffer.size() >= 1u);
15345
15346 // skip past any whitespace that followed the key
15347 consume_leading_whitespace();
15348 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15349
15350 // '='
15351 if (*cp != U'=')
15352 set_error_and_return_default("expected '=', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15353 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15354
15355 // skip past any whitespace that followed the '='
15356 consume_leading_whitespace();
15357 return_if_error({});
15358 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15359
15360 // check that the next character could actually be a value
15361 if (is_value_terminator(*cp))
15362 set_error_and_return_default("expected value, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15363
15364 // if it's a dotted kvp we need to spawn the parent sub-tables if necessary,
15365 // and set the target table to the second-to-last one in the chain
15366 if (key_buffer.size() > 1u)
15367 {
15368 for (size_t i = 0; i < key_buffer.size() - 1u; i++)
15369 {
15370 const std::string_view segment = key_buffer[i];
15371 auto pit = tbl->lower_bound(segment);
15372
15373 // parent already existed
15374 if (pit != tbl->end() && pit->first == segment)
15375 {
15376 table* p = pit->second.as_table();
15377
15378 // redefinition
15379 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!p
15380 || !(impl::find(dotted_key_tables.begin(), dotted_key_tables.end(), p)
15381 || impl::find(implicit_tables.begin(), implicit_tables.end(), p)))
15382 {
15383 set_error_at(key_buffer.starts[i],
15384 "cannot redefine existing "sv,
15385 to_sv(pit->second.type()),
15386 " as dotted key-value pair"sv);
15387 return_after_error({});
15388 }
15389
15390 tbl = p;
15391 }
15392
15393 // need to create a new implicit table
15394 else
15395 {
15396 pit = tbl->emplace_hint<table>(pit, make_key(i));
15397 table& p = pit->second.ref_cast<table>();
15398 p.source_ = pit->first.source();
15399
15400 dotted_key_tables.push_back(&p);
15401 tbl = &p;
15402 }
15403 }
15404 }
15405
15406 // ensure this isn't a redefinition
15407 const std::string_view last_segment = key_buffer.back();
15408 auto it = tbl->lower_bound(last_segment);
15409 if (it != tbl->end() && it->first == last_segment)
15410 {
15411 set_error("cannot redefine existing "sv,
15412 to_sv(it->second.type()),
15413 " '"sv,
15414 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15415 "'"sv);
15416 return_after_error({});
15417 }
15418
15419 // create the key first since the key buffer will likely get overwritten during value parsing (inline
15420 // tables)
15421 auto last_key = make_key(key_buffer.size() - 1u);
15422
15423 // now we can actually parse the value
15424 node_ptr val = parse_value();
15425 return_if_error({});
15426
15427 tbl->emplace_hint<node_ptr>(it, std::move(last_key), std::move(val));
15428 return true;
15429 }
15430
15431 void parse_document()
15432 {
15433 assert_not_error();
15434 assert_not_eof();
15435 push_parse_scope("root table"sv);
15436
15437 table* current_table = &root;
15438
15439 do
15440 {
15441 return_if_error();
15442
15443 // leading whitespace, line endings, comments
15444 if (consume_leading_whitespace() || consume_line_break() || consume_comment())
15445 continue;
15446 return_if_error();
15447
15448 // [tables]
15449 // [[table array]]
15450 if (*cp == U'[')
15451 current_table = parse_table_header();
15452
15453 // bare_keys
15454 // dotted.keys
15455 // "quoted keys"
15456 else if (is_bare_key_character(*cp) || is_string_delimiter(*cp))
15457 {
15458 push_parse_scope("key-value pair"sv);
15459
15460 parse_key_value_pair_and_insert(current_table);
15461
15462 // handle the rest of the line after the kvp
15463 // (this is not done in parse_key_value_pair() because that is also used for inline tables)
15464 consume_leading_whitespace();
15465 return_if_error();
15466 if (!is_eof() && !consume_comment() && !consume_line_break())
15467 set_error("expected a comment or whitespace, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
15468 }
15469
15470 else // ??
15471 set_error("expected keys, tables, whitespace or comments, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
15472 } while (!is_eof());
15473
15474 auto eof_pos = current_position(1);
15475 root.source_.end = eof_pos;
15476 if (current_table && current_table != &root && current_table->source_.end <= current_table->source_.begin)
15477 current_table->source_.end = eof_pos;
15478 }
15479
15480 static void update_region_ends(node& nde) noexcept
15481 {
15482 const auto type = nde.type();
15483 if (type > node_type::array)
15484 return;
15485
15486 if (type == node_type::table)
15487 {
15488 auto& tbl = nde.ref_cast<table>();
15489 if (tbl.is_inline()) // inline tables (and all their inline descendants) are already correctly
15490 // terminated
15491 return;
15492
15493 auto end = nde.source_.end;
15494 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
15495 {
15496 TOML_UNUSED(k);
15497 update_region_ends(v);
15498 if (end < v.source_.end)
15499 end = v.source_.end;
15500 }
15501 }
15502 else // arrays
15503 {
15504 auto& arr = nde.ref_cast<array>();
15505 auto end = nde.source_.end;
15506 for (auto&& v : arr)
15507 {
15508 update_region_ends(v);
15509 if (end < v.source_.end)
15510 end = v.source_.end;
15511 }
15512 nde.source_.end = end;
15513 }
15514 }
15515
15516 public:
15517 parser(utf8_reader_interface&& reader_) //
15518 : reader{ reader_ }
15519 {
15520 root.source_ = { prev_pos, prev_pos, reader.source_path() };
15521
15522 if (!reader.peek_eof())
15523 {
15524 cp = reader.read_next();
15525
15526 #if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15527 if (reader.error())
15528 {
15529 err = std::move(reader.error());
15530 return;
15531 }
15532 #endif
15533
15534 if (cp)
15535 parse_document();
15536 }
15537
15538 update_region_ends(root);
15539 }
15540
15541 TOML_NODISCARD
15542 operator parse_result() && noexcept
15543 {
15544 #if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15545
15546 return { std::move(root) };
15547
15548 #else
15549
15550 if (err)
15551 return parse_result{ *std::move(err) };
15552 else
15553 return parse_result{ std::move(root) };
15554
15555 #endif
15556 }
15557 };
15558
15559 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15560 node_ptr parser::parse_array()
15561 {
15562 return_if_error({});
15563 assert_not_eof();
15564 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'[');
15565 push_parse_scope("array"sv);
15566
15567 // skip opening '['
15568 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15569
15570 node_ptr arr_ptr{ new array{} };
15571 array& arr = arr_ptr->ref_cast<array>();
15572 enum class TOML_CLOSED_ENUM parse_type : int
15573 {
15574 none,
15575 comma,
15576 val
15577 };
15578 parse_type prev = parse_type::none;
15579
15580 while (!is_error())
15581 {
15582 while (consume_leading_whitespace() || consume_line_break() || consume_comment())
15583 continue;
15584 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15585
15586 // commas - only legal after a value
15587 if (*cp == U',')
15588 {
15589 if (prev == parse_type::val)
15590 {
15591 prev = parse_type::comma;
15592 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15593 continue;
15594 }
15595 set_error_and_return_default("expected value or closing ']', saw comma"sv);
15596 }
15597
15598 // closing ']'
15599 else if (*cp == U']')
15600 {
15601 advance_and_return_if_error({});
15602 break;
15603 }
15604
15605 // must be a value
15606 else
15607 {
15608 if (prev == parse_type::val)
15609 {
15610 set_error_and_return_default("expected comma or closing ']', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15611 continue;
15612 }
15613 prev = parse_type::val;
15614
15615 auto val = parse_value();
15616 return_if_error({});
15617
15618 if (!arr.capacity())
15619 arr.reserve(4u);
15620 arr.emplace_back<node_ptr>(std::move(val));
15621 }
15622 }
15623
15624 return_if_error({});
15625 return arr_ptr;
15626 }
15627
15628 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15629 node_ptr parser::parse_inline_table()
15630 {
15631 return_if_error({});
15632 assert_not_eof();
15633 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'{');
15634 push_parse_scope("inline table"sv);
15635
15636 // skip opening '{'
15637 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15638
15639 node_ptr tbl_ptr{ new table{} };
15640 table& tbl = tbl_ptr->ref_cast<table>();
15641 tbl.is_inline(true);
15642 table_vector_scope table_scope{ open_inline_tables, tbl };
15643
15644 enum class TOML_CLOSED_ENUM parse_type : int
15645 {
15646 none,
15647 comma,
15648 kvp
15649 };
15650 parse_type prev = parse_type::none;
15651 while (!is_error())
15652 {
15653 if constexpr (TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED) // toml/issues/516 (newlines/trailing commas in inline tables)
15654 {
15655 while (consume_leading_whitespace() || consume_line_break() || consume_comment())
15656 continue;
15657 }
15658 else
15659 {
15660 while (consume_leading_whitespace())
15661 continue;
15662 }
15663 return_if_error({});
15664 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15665
15666 // commas - only legal after a key-value pair
15667 if (*cp == U',')
15668 {
15669 if (prev == parse_type::kvp)
15670 {
15671 prev = parse_type::comma;
15672 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15673 }
15674 else
15675 set_error_and_return_default("expected key-value pair or closing '}', saw comma"sv);
15676 }
15677
15678 // closing '}'
15679 else if (*cp == U'}')
15680 {
15681 if constexpr (!TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED) // toml/issues/516 (newlines/trailing commas in inline tables)
15682 {
15683 if (prev == parse_type::comma)
15684 {
15685 set_error_and_return_default("expected key-value pair, saw closing '}' (dangling comma)"sv);
15686 continue;
15687 }
15688 }
15689 advance_and_return_if_error({});
15690 break;
15691 }
15692
15693 // key-value pair
15694 else if (is_string_delimiter(*cp) || is_bare_key_character(*cp))
15695 {
15696 if (prev == parse_type::kvp)
15697 set_error_and_return_default("expected comma or closing '}', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15698 else
15699 {
15700 prev = parse_type::kvp;
15701 parse_key_value_pair_and_insert(&tbl);
15702 }
15703 }
15704
15705 else
15706 set_error_and_return_default("expected key or closing '}', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15707 }
15708
15709 return_if_error({});
15710 return tbl_ptr;
15711 }
15712
15713 TOML_ABI_NAMESPACE_END; // TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15714}
15715TOML_IMPL_NAMESPACE_END;
15716
15717#undef TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
15718#undef advance_and_return_if_error
15719#undef advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof
15720#undef assert_not_eof
15721#undef assert_not_error
15722#undef is_eof
15723#undef is_error
15724#undef parse_error_break
15725#undef push_parse_scope
15726#undef push_parse_scope_1
15727#undef push_parse_scope_2

15729#undef return_if_eof
15730#undef return_if_error

15733#undef set_error_and_return_default

15742 TOML_NODISCARD
15743 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
15744 parse_result do_parse(utf8_reader_interface && reader)
15745 {
15746 return impl::parser{ std::move(reader) };
15747 }
15748
15749 TOML_NODISCARD
15750 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
15751 parse_result do_parse_file(std::string_view file_path)
15752 {
15753#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15754#define TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR(msg, path) \
15755 throw parse_error{ msg, source_position{}, std::make_shared<const std::string>(std::move(path)) }
15756#else
15757#define TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR(msg, path) \
15758 return parse_result \
15759 { \
15760 parse_error \
15761 { \
15762 msg, source_position{}, std::make_shared<const std::string>(std::move(path)) \
15763 } \
15764 }
15765#endif
15766
15767 std::string file_path_str(file_path);
15768
15769 // open file with a custom-sized stack buffer
15770 std::ifstream file;
15771 TOML_OVERALIGNED char file_buffer[sizeof(void*) * 1024u];
15772 file.rdbuf()->pubsetbuf(file_buffer, sizeof(file_buffer));
15773#if TOML_WINDOWS
15774 file.open(impl::widen(file_path_str).c_str(), std::ifstream::in | std::ifstream::binary | std::ifstream::ate);
15775#else
15776 file.open(file_path_str, std::ifstream::in | std::ifstream::binary | std::ifstream::ate);
15777#endif
15778 if (!file.is_open())
15779 TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR("File could not be opened for reading", file_path_str);
15780
15781 // get size
15782 const auto file_size = file.tellg();
15783 if (file_size == -1)
15784 TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR("Could not determine file size", file_path_str);
15785 file.seekg(0, std::ifstream::beg);
15786
15787 // read the whole file into memory first if the file isn't too large
15788 constexpr auto large_file_threshold = 1024 * 1024 * 2; // 2 MB
15789 if (file_size <= large_file_threshold)
15790 {
15791 std::vector<char> file_data;
15792 file_data.resize(static_cast<size_t>(file_size));
15793 file.read(file_data.data(), static_cast<std::streamsize>(file_size));
15794 return parse(std::string_view{ file_data.data(), file_data.size() }, std::move(file_path_str));
15795 }
15796
15797 // otherwise parse it using the streams
15798 else
15799 return parse(file, std::move(file_path_str));
15800
15801#undef TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR
15802 }
15803}
15804TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_END;
15805
15806TOML_NAMESPACE_START

15808 TOML_ABI_NAMESPACE_BOOL(TOML_EXCEPTIONS, ex, noex);

15926{
15927 enum class TOML_CLOSED_FLAGS_ENUM formatted_string_traits : unsigned
15928 {
15929 none,
15930 line_breaks = 1u << 0, // \n
15931 tabs = 1u << 1, // \t
15932 control_chars = 1u << 2, // also includes non-ascii vertical whitespace
15933 single_quotes = 1u << 3,
15934 non_bare = 1u << 4, // anything not satisfying "is bare key character"
15935 non_ascii = 1u << 5, // any codepoint >= 128
15936
15937 all = (non_ascii << 1u) - 1u
15938 };
15939 TOML_MAKE_FLAGS(formatted_string_traits);
15940
15941 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15942 formatter::formatter(const node* source_node,
15943 const parse_result* source_pr,
15944 const formatter_constants& constants,
15945 const formatter_config& config) noexcept //
15946#if TOML_ENABLE_PARSER && !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15947 : source_{ source_pr && *source_pr ? &source_pr->table() : source_node },
15948 result_{ source_pr },
15949#else
15950 : source_{ source_pr ? source_pr : source_node },
15951#endif
15952 constants_{ &constants },
15953 config_{ config }
15954 {
15955 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(source_);
15956
15957 config_.flags = (config_.flags | constants_->mandatory_flags) & ~constants_->ignored_flags;
15958
15959 indent_columns_ = {};
15960 for (auto c : config_.indent)
15961 indent_columns_ += c == '\t' ? 4u : 1u;
15962
15963 int_format_mask_ = config_.flags
15964 & (format_flags::allow_binary_integers | format_flags::allow_octal_integers
15965 | format_flags::allow_hexadecimal_integers);
15966 }

15969 void formatter::attach(std::ostream& stream) noexcept
15970 {
15971 indent_ = {};
15972 naked_newline_ = true;
15973 stream_ = &stream;
15974 }
15975
15976 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15977 void formatter::detach() noexcept
15978 {
15979 stream_ = nullptr;
15980 }

16009 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE

16015
16016 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16017 void formatter::print_string(std::string_view str, bool allow_multi_line, bool allow_bare)
16018 {
16019 if (str.empty())
16020 {
16021 print_unformatted(literal_strings_allowed() ? "''"sv : "\"\""sv);
16022 return;
16023 }
16024
16025 // pre-scan the string to determine how we should output it
16026 formatted_string_traits traits = {};
16027
16028 if (!allow_bare)
16029 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16030 bool unicode_allowed = unicode_strings_allowed();
16031
16032 // ascii fast path
16033 if (is_ascii(str.data(), str.length()))
16034 {
16035 for (auto c : str)
16036 {
16037 switch (c)
16038 {
16039 case '\n': traits |= formatted_string_traits::line_breaks; break;
16040 case '\t': traits |= formatted_string_traits::tabs; break;
16041 case '\'': traits |= formatted_string_traits::single_quotes; break;
16042 default:
16043 {
16044 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_control_character(c))
16045 traits |= formatted_string_traits::control_chars;
16046
16047 if (!is_ascii_bare_key_character(static_cast<char32_t>(c)))
16048 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16049 break;
16050 }
16051 }
16052
16053 static constexpr auto all_ascii_traits =
16054 formatted_string_traits::all & ~formatted_string_traits::non_ascii;
16055 if (traits == all_ascii_traits)
16056 break;
16057 }
16058 }
16059
16060 // unicode slow path
16061 else
16062 {
16063 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_ascii;
16064 utf8_decoder decoder;
16065
16066 // if the unicode is malformed just treat the string as a single-line non-literal and
16067 // escape all non-ascii characters (to ensure round-tripping and help with diagnostics)
16068 const auto bad_unicode = [&]() noexcept
16069 {
16070 traits &= ~formatted_string_traits::line_breaks;
16071 traits |= formatted_string_traits::control_chars | formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16072 unicode_allowed = false;
16073 };
16074
16075 for (auto c : str)
16076 {
16077 decoder(c);
16078
16079 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder.error())
16080 {
16081 bad_unicode();
16082 break;
16083 }
16084
16085 if (!decoder.has_code_point())
16086 continue;
16087
16088 switch (decoder.codepoint)
16089 {
16090 case U'\n': traits |= formatted_string_traits::line_breaks; break;
16091 case U'\t': traits |= formatted_string_traits::tabs; break;
16092 case U'\'': traits |= formatted_string_traits::single_quotes; break;
16093 default:
16094 {
16095 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_control_character(decoder.codepoint)
16096 || is_non_ascii_vertical_whitespace(decoder.codepoint))
16097 traits |= formatted_string_traits::control_chars;
16098
16099 if (!is_bare_key_character(decoder.codepoint))
16100 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16101 break;
16102 }
16103 }
16104 }
16105
16106 if (decoder.needs_more_input())
16107 bad_unicode();
16108 }
16109
16110 // if the string meets the requirements of being 'bare' we can emit a bare string
16111 // (bare strings are composed of letters and numbers; no whitespace, control chars, quotes, etc)
16112 if (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_bare)
16113 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_ascii) || unicode_allowed))
16114 {
16115 print_unformatted(str);
16116 return;
16117 }
16118
16119 // determine if this should be a multi-line string (triple-quotes)
16120 const auto multi_line = allow_multi_line //
16121 && multi_line_strings_allowed() //
16122 && !!(traits & formatted_string_traits::line_breaks);
16123
16124 // determine if this should be a literal string (single-quotes with no escaping)
16125 const auto literal = literal_strings_allowed() //
16126 && !(traits & formatted_string_traits::control_chars) //
16127 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::single_quotes) || multi_line) //
16128 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::tabs) || real_tabs_in_strings_allowed()) //
16129 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_ascii) || unicode_allowed);
16130
16131 // literal strings (single quotes, no escape codes)
16132 if (literal)
16133 {
16134 const auto quot = multi_line ? R"(''')"sv : R"(')"sv;
16135 print_unformatted(quot);
16136 print_unformatted(str);
16137 print_unformatted(quot);
16138 return;
16139 }
16140
16141 // anything from here down is a non-literal string, so requires iteration and escaping.
16142 print_unformatted(multi_line ? R"(""")"sv : R"(")"sv);
16143
16144 const auto real_tabs_allowed = real_tabs_in_strings_allowed();
16145
16146 // ascii fast path
16147 if (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_ascii))
16148 {
16149 for (auto c : str)
16150 {
16151 switch (c)
16152 {
16153 case '"': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\")"sv); break;
16154 case '\\': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\\)"sv); break;
16155 case '\x7F': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u007F)"sv); break;
16156 case '\t': print_to_stream(*stream_, real_tabs_allowed ? "\t"sv : R"(\t)"sv); break;
16157 case '\n': print_to_stream(*stream_, multi_line ? "\n"sv : R"(\n)"sv); break;
16158 default:
16159 {
16160 // control characters from lookup table
16161 if TOML_UNLIKELY(c >= '\x00' && c <= '\x1F')
16162 print_to_stream(*stream_, control_char_escapes[c]);
16163
16164 // regular characters
16165 else
16166 print_to_stream(*stream_, c);
16167 }
16168 }
16169 }
16170 }
16171
16172 // unicode slow path
16173 else
16174 {
16175 utf8_decoder decoder;
16176 const char* cp_start = str.data();
16177 const char* cp_end = cp_start;
16178 for (auto c : str)
16179 {
16180 decoder(c);
16181 cp_end++;
16182
16183 // if the decoder encounters malformed unicode just emit raw bytes and
16184 if (decoder.error())
16185 {
16186 while (cp_start != cp_end)
16187 {
16188 print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u00)"sv);
16189 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16190 static_cast<uint8_t>(*cp_start),
16191 value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal,
16192 2);
16193 cp_start++;
16194 }
16195 decoder.reset();
16196 continue;
16197 }
16198
16199 if (!decoder.has_code_point())
16200 continue;
16201
16202 switch (decoder.codepoint)
16203 {
16204 case U'"': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\")"sv); break;
16205 case U'\\': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\\)"sv); break;
16206 case U'\x7F': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u007F)"sv); break;
16207 case U'\t': print_to_stream(*stream_, real_tabs_allowed ? "\t"sv : R"(\t)"sv); break;
16208 case U'\n': print_to_stream(*stream_, multi_line ? "\n"sv : R"(\n)"sv); break;
16209 default:
16210 {
16211 // control characters from lookup table
16212 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder.codepoint <= U'\x1F')
16213 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16214 control_char_escapes[static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint)]);
16215
16216 // escaped unicode characters
16217 else if (decoder.codepoint > U'\x7F'
16218 && (!unicode_allowed || is_non_ascii_vertical_whitespace(decoder.codepoint)))
16219 {
16220 if (static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint) > 0xFFFFu)
16221 {
16222 print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\U)"sv);
16223 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16224 static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint),
16225 value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal,
16226 8);
16227 }
16228 else
16229 {
16230 print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u)"sv);
16231 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16232 static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint),
16233 value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal,
16234 4);
16235 }
16236 }
16237
16238 // regular characters
16239 else
16240 print_to_stream(*stream_, cp_start, static_cast<size_t>(cp_end - cp_start));
16241 }
16242 }
16243
16244 cp_start = cp_end;
16245 }
16246 }
16247
16248 print_unformatted(multi_line ? R"(""")"sv : R"(")"sv);
16249 }
16250
16251 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16252 void formatter::print(const value<std::string>& val)
16253 {
16254 print_string(val.get());
16255 }
16256
16257 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16258 void formatter::print(const value<int64_t>& val)
16259 {
16260 naked_newline_ = false;
16261
16262 if (*val >= 0 && !!int_format_mask_)
16263 {
16264 static constexpr auto value_flags_mask =
16265 value_flags::format_as_binary | value_flags::format_as_octal | value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal;
16266
16267 const auto fmt = val.flags() & value_flags_mask;
16268 switch (fmt)
16269 {
16270 case value_flags::format_as_binary:
16271 if (!!(int_format_mask_ & format_flags::allow_binary_integers))
16272 {
16273 print_to_stream(*stream_, "0b"sv);
16274 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val, fmt);
16275 return;
16276 }
16277 break;
16278
16279 case value_flags::format_as_octal:
16280 if (!!(int_format_mask_ & format_flags::allow_octal_integers))
16281 {
16282 print_to_stream(*stream_, "0o"sv);
16283 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val, fmt);
16284 return;
16285 }
16286 break;
16287
16288 case value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal:
16289 if (!!(int_format_mask_ & format_flags::allow_hexadecimal_integers))
16290 {
16291 print_to_stream(*stream_, "0x"sv);
16292 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val, fmt);
16293 return;
16294 }
16295 break;
16296
16297 default: break;
16298 }
16299 }
16300
16301 // fallback to decimal
16302 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val);
16303 }
16304
16305 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16306 void formatter::print(const value<double>& val)
16307 {
16308 const std::string_view* inf_nan = nullptr;
16309 switch (fpclassify(*val))
16310 {
16311 case fp_class::neg_inf: inf_nan = &constants_->float_neg_inf; break;
16312 case fp_class::pos_inf: inf_nan = &constants_->float_pos_inf; break;
16313 case fp_class::nan: inf_nan = &constants_->float_nan; break;
16314 case fp_class::ok:
16315 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16316 *val,
16317 value_flags::none,
16318 !!(config_.flags & format_flags::relaxed_float_precision));
16319 break;
16320 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16321 }
16322
16323 if (inf_nan)
16324 {
16325 if (!!(config_.flags & format_flags::quote_infinities_and_nans))
16326 print_to_stream_bookended(*stream_, *inf_nan, '"');
16327 else
16328 print_to_stream(*stream_, *inf_nan);
16329 }
16330
16331 naked_newline_ = false;
16332 }
16333
16334 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16335 void formatter::print(const value<bool>& val)
16336 {
16337 print_unformatted(*val ? constants_->bool_true : constants_->bool_false);
16338 }
16339

16341 void formatter::print(const value<date>& val)
16342 {
16343 if (!!(config_.flags & format_flags::quote_dates_and_times))
16344 print_to_stream_bookended(*stream_, *val, literal_strings_allowed() ? '\'' : '"');
16345 else
16346 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val);
16347 naked_newline_ = false;
16348 }

16370 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16371 void formatter::print_value(const node& val_node, node_type type)
16372 {
16373 TOML_ASSUME(type > node_type::array);
16374 switch (type)
16375 {
16376 case node_type::string: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&val_node)); break;
16377 case node_type::integer: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<int64_t>*>(&val_node)); break;
16378 case node_type::floating_point: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<double>*>(&val_node)); break;
16379 case node_type::boolean: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<bool>*>(&val_node)); break;
16380 case node_type::date: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<date>*>(&val_node)); break;
16381 case node_type::time: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<time>*>(&val_node)); break;
16382 case node_type::date_time: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<date_time>*>(&val_node)); break;
16383 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16384 }
16385 }

16427#ifdef _MSC_VER
16428#pragma inline_recursion(on)
16429#pragma push_macro("min")
16430#pragma push_macro("max")

16437TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_START
16438{
16439 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
16440 size_t toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(const node & node, size_t line_wrap_cols) noexcept
16441 {
16442 switch (node.type())
16443 {
16444 case node_type::table:
16445 {
16446 auto& tbl = *reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&node);
16447 if (tbl.empty())
16448 return 2u; // "{}"
16449 size_t weight = 3u; // "{ }"
16450 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16451 {
16452 weight += k.length() + toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(v, line_wrap_cols) + 2u; // + ", "
16453 if (weight >= line_wrap_cols)
16454 break;
16455 }
16456 return weight;
16457 }
16458
16459 case node_type::array:
16460 {
16461 auto& arr = *reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&node);
16462 if (arr.empty())
16463 return 2u; // "[]"
16464 size_t weight = 3u; // "[ ]"
16465 for (auto& elem : arr)
16466 {
16467 weight += toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(elem, line_wrap_cols) + 2u; // + ", "
16468 if (weight >= line_wrap_cols)
16469 break;
16470 }
16471 return weight;
16472 }
16473
16474 case node_type::string:
16475 {
16476 // todo: proper utf8 decoding?
16477 // todo: tab awareness?
16478 auto& str = (*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&node)).get();
16479 return str.length() + 2u; // + ""
16480 }
16481
16482 case node_type::integer:
16483 {
16484 auto val = (*reinterpret_cast<const value<int64_t>*>(&node)).get();
16485 if (!val)
16486 return 1u;
16487 size_t weight = {};
16488 if (val < 0)
16489 {
16490 weight += 1u;
16491 val *= -1;
16492 }
16493 return weight + static_cast<size_t>(log10(static_cast<double>(val))) + 1u;
16494 }
16495
16496 case node_type::floating_point:
16497 {
16498 auto val = (*reinterpret_cast<const value<double>*>(&node)).get();
16499 if (val == 0.0)
16500 return 3u; // "0.0"
16501 size_t weight = 2u; // ".0"
16502 if (val < 0.0)
16503 {
16504 weight += 1u;
16505 val *= -1.0;
16506 }
16507 return weight + static_cast<size_t>(log10(val)) + 1u;
16508 break;
16509 }
16510
16511 case node_type::boolean: return 5u;
16512 case node_type::date: [[fallthrough]];
16513 case node_type::time: return 10u;
16514 case node_type::date_time: return 30u;
16515 case node_type::none: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16516 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16517 }
16518
16519 TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16520 }
16521
16522 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
16523 bool toml_formatter_forces_multiline(const node & node, size_t line_wrap_cols, size_t starting_column_bias) noexcept
16524 {
16525 return (toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(node, line_wrap_cols) + starting_column_bias) >= line_wrap_cols;
16526 }
16527}

16531{
16532 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16533 void toml_formatter::print_pending_table_separator()
16534 {
16535 if (pending_table_separator_)
16536 {
16537 print_newline(true);
16538 print_newline(true);
16539 pending_table_separator_ = false;
16540 }
16541 }

16544 void toml_formatter::print(const key & k)
16545 {
16546 print_string(k.str(), false, true);

16548
16549 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16550 void toml_formatter::print_inline(const table & tbl)
16551 {
16552 if (tbl.empty())
16553 {
16554 print_unformatted("{}"sv);
16555 return;
16556 }
16557
16558 print_unformatted("{ "sv);
16559
16560 bool first = false;
16561 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16562 {
16563 if (first)
16564 print_unformatted(", "sv);
16565 first = true;
16566
16567 print(k);
16568 if (terse_kvps())
16569 print_unformatted("="sv);
16570 else
16571 print_unformatted(" = "sv);
16572
16573 const auto type = v.type();
16574 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16575 switch (type)
16576 {
16577 case node_type::table: print_inline(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16578 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16579 default: print_value(v, type);
16580 }
16581 }
16582
16583 print_unformatted(" }"sv);
16584 }
16585
16586 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16587 void toml_formatter::print(const array & arr)
16588 {
16589 if (arr.empty())
16590 {
16591 print_unformatted("[]"sv);
16592 return;
16593 }
16594
16595 const auto original_indent = indent();
16596 const auto multiline = TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE::toml_formatter_forces_multiline(
16597 arr,
16598 120u,
16599 indent_columns() * static_cast<size_t>(original_indent < 0 ? 0 : original_indent));
16600
16601 print_unformatted("["sv);
16602
16603 if (multiline)
16604 {
16605 if (original_indent < 0)
16606 indent(0);
16607 if (indent_array_elements())
16608 increase_indent();
16609 }
16610 else
16611 print_unformatted(' ');
16612
16613 for (size_t i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++)
16614 {
16615 if (i > 0u)
16616 {
16617 print_unformatted(',');
16618 if (!multiline)
16619 print_unformatted(' ');
16620 }
16621
16622 if (multiline)
16623 {
16624 print_newline(true);
16625 print_indent();
16626 }
16627
16628 auto& v = arr[i];
16629 const auto type = v.type();
16630 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16631 switch (type)
16632 {
16633 case node_type::table: print_inline(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16634 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16635 default: print_value(v, type);
16636 }
16637 }
16638 if (multiline)
16639 {
16640 indent(original_indent);
16641 print_newline(true);
16642 print_indent();
16643 }
16644 else
16645 print_unformatted(' ');
16646
16647 print_unformatted("]"sv);
16648 }
16649
16650 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16651 void toml_formatter::print(const table & tbl)
16652 {
16653 static constexpr auto is_non_inline_array_of_tables = [](const node& n) noexcept
16654 {
16655 const auto arr = n.as_array();
16656 if (!arr || !arr->is_array_of_tables())
16657 return false;
16658
16659 return !reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&(*arr)[0])->is_inline();
16660 };
16661
16662 // values, arrays, and inline tables/table arrays
16663 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16664 {
16665 const auto type = v.type();
16666 if ((type == node_type::table && !reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)->is_inline())
16667 || (type == node_type::array && is_non_inline_array_of_tables(v)))
16668 continue;
16669
16670 pending_table_separator_ = true;
16671 print_newline();
16672 print_indent();
16673 print(k);
16674 if (terse_kvps())
16675 print_unformatted("="sv);
16676 else
16677 print_unformatted(" = "sv);
16678 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16679 switch (type)
16680 {
16681 case node_type::table: print_inline(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16682 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16683 default: print_value(v, type);
16684 }
16685 }
16686
16687 const auto print_key_path = [&]()
16688 {
16689 size_t i{};
16690 for (const auto k : key_path_)
16691 {
16692 if (i++)
16693 print_unformatted('.');
16694 print(*k);
16695 }
16696 };
16697
16698 // non-inline tables
16699 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16700 {
16701 const auto type = v.type();
16702 if (type != node_type::table || reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)->is_inline())
16703 continue;
16704 auto& child_tbl = *reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v);
16705
16706 // we can skip indenting and emitting the headers for tables that only contain other tables
16707 // (so we don't over-nest)
16708 size_t child_value_count{}; // includes inline tables and non-table arrays
16709 size_t child_table_count{};
16710 size_t child_table_array_count{};
16711 for (auto&& [child_k, child_v] : child_tbl)
16712 {
16713 TOML_UNUSED(child_k);
16714 const auto child_type = child_v.type();
16715 TOML_ASSUME(child_type != node_type::none);
16716 switch (child_type)
16717 {
16718 case node_type::table:
16719 if (reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&child_v)->is_inline())
16720 child_value_count++;
16721 else
16722 child_table_count++;
16723 break;
16724
16725 case node_type::array:
16726 if (is_non_inline_array_of_tables(child_v))
16727 child_table_array_count++;
16728 else
16729 child_value_count++;
16730 break;
16731
16732 default: child_value_count++;
16733 }
16734 }
16735 bool skip_self = false;
16736 if (child_value_count == 0u && (child_table_count > 0u || child_table_array_count > 0u))
16737 skip_self = true;
16738
16739 key_path_.push_back(&k);
16740
16741 if (!skip_self)
16742 {
16743 print_pending_table_separator();
16744 if (indent_sub_tables())
16745 increase_indent();
16746 print_indent();
16747 print_unformatted("["sv);
16748 print_key_path();
16749 print_unformatted("]"sv);
16750 pending_table_separator_ = true;
16751 }
16752
16753 print(child_tbl);
16754
16755 key_path_.pop_back();
16756 if (!skip_self && indent_sub_tables())
16757 decrease_indent();
16758 }
16759
16760 // table arrays
16761 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16762 {
16763 if (!is_non_inline_array_of_tables(v))
16764 continue;
16765 auto& arr = *reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v);
16766
16767 if (indent_sub_tables())
16768 increase_indent();
16769 key_path_.push_back(&k);
16770
16771 for (size_t i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++)
16772 {
16773 print_pending_table_separator();
16774 print_indent();
16775 print_unformatted("[["sv);
16776 print_key_path();
16777 print_unformatted("]]"sv);
16778 pending_table_separator_ = true;
16779 print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&arr[i]));
16780 }
16781
16782 key_path_.pop_back();
16783 if (indent_sub_tables())
16784 decrease_indent();
16785 }
16786 }
16787
16788 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16789 void toml_formatter::print()
16790 {
16791 if (dump_failed_parse_result())
16792 return;
16793
16794 switch (auto source_type = source().type())
16795 {
16796 case node_type::table:
16797 {
16798 auto& tbl = *reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&source());
16799 if (tbl.is_inline())
16800 print_inline(tbl);
16801 else
16802 {
16803 decrease_indent(); // so root kvps and tables have the same indent
16804 print(tbl);
16805 }
16806 break;
16807 }
16808
16809 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&source())); break;
16810
16811 default: print_value(source(), source_type);
16812 }
16813 }
16814}

16840{
16841 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16842 void json_formatter::print(const toml::table & tbl)
16843 {
16844 if (tbl.empty())
16845 {
16846 print_unformatted("{}"sv);
16847 return;
16848 }
16849
16850 print_unformatted('{');
16851
16852 if (indent_sub_tables())
16853 increase_indent();
16854 bool first = false;
16855 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16856 {
16857 if (first)
16858 print_unformatted(',');
16859 first = true;
16860 print_newline(true);
16861 print_indent();
16862
16863 print_string(k.str(), false);
16864 if (terse_kvps())
16865 print_unformatted(":"sv);
16866 else
16867 print_unformatted(" : "sv);
16868
16869 const auto type = v.type();
16870 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16871 switch (type)
16872 {
16873 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16874 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16875 default: print_value(v, type);
16876 }
16877 }
16878 if (indent_sub_tables())
16879 decrease_indent();
16880 print_newline(true);
16881 print_indent();
16882
16883 print_unformatted('}');
16884 }

16891 print_unformatted("[]"sv);
16892 return;

16896 if (indent_array_elements())
16897 increase_indent();
16898 for (size_t i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++)
16899 {
16900 if (i > 0u)
16901 print_unformatted(',');
16902 print_newline(true);
16903 print_indent();
16904
16905 auto& v = arr[i];
16906 const auto type = v.type();
16907 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16908 switch (type)
16909 {
16910 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16911 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16912 default: print_value(v, type);
16913 }
16914 }
16915 if (indent_array_elements())
16916 decrease_indent();
16917 print_newline(true);
16918 print_indent();
16919 print_unformatted(']');
16920 }

16961{
16962 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16963 void yaml_formatter::print_yaml_string(const value<std::string>&str)
16964 {
16965 if (str->empty())
16966 {
16967 base::print(str);
16968 return;
16969 }
16970
16971 bool contains_newline = false;
16972 for (auto c = str->c_str(), e = str->c_str() + str->length(); c < e && !contains_newline; c++)
16973 contains_newline = *c == '\n';
16974
16975 if (contains_newline)
16976 {
16977 print_unformatted("|-"sv);
16978
16979 increase_indent();
16980
16981 auto line_end = str->c_str() - 1u;
16982 const auto end = str->c_str() + str->length();
16983 while (line_end != end)
16984 {
16985 auto line_start = line_end + 1u;
16986 line_end = line_start;
16987 for (; line_end != end && *line_end != '\n'; line_end++)
16988 ;
16989
16990 if TOML_LIKELY(line_start != line_end || line_end != end)
16991 {
16992 print_newline();
16993 print_indent();
16994 print_unformatted(std::string_view{ line_start, static_cast<size_t>(line_end - line_start) });
16995 }
16996 }
16997
16998 decrease_indent();
16999 }
17000 else
17001 print_string(*str, false, true);
17002 }
17003
17004 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
17005 void yaml_formatter::print(const toml::table & tbl, bool parent_is_array)
17006 {
17007 if (tbl.empty())
17008 {
17009 print_unformatted("{}"sv);
17010 return;
17011 }
17012
17013 increase_indent();
17014
17015 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
17016 {
17017 if (!parent_is_array)
17018 {
17019 print_newline();
17020 print_indent();
17021 }
17022 parent_is_array = false;
17023
17024 print_string(k.str(), false, true);
17025 if (terse_kvps())
17026 print_unformatted(":"sv);
17027 else
17028 print_unformatted(": "sv);
17029
17030 const auto type = v.type();
17031 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
17032 switch (type)
17033 {
17034 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
17035 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
17036 case node_type::string: print_yaml_string(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&v)); break;
17037 default: print_value(v, type);
17038 }
17039 }
17040
17041 decrease_indent();
17042 }
17043
17044 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
17045 void yaml_formatter::print(const toml::array & arr, bool parent_is_array)
17046 {
17047 if (arr.empty())
17048 {
17049 print_unformatted("[]"sv);
17050 return;
17051 }
17052
17053 increase_indent();
17054
17055 for (auto&& v : arr)
17056 {
17057 if (!parent_is_array)
17058 {
17059 print_newline();
17060 print_indent();
17061 }
17062 parent_is_array = false;
17063
17064 print_unformatted("- "sv);
17065
17066 const auto type = v.type();
17067 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
17068 switch (type)
17069 {
17070 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v), true); break;
17071 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v), true); break;
17072 case node_type::string: print_yaml_string(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&v)); break;
17073 default: print_value(v, type);
17074 }
17075 }
17076
17077 decrease_indent();
17078 }
17079
17080 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
17081 void yaml_formatter::print()
17082 {
17083 if (dump_failed_parse_result())
17084 return;
17085
17086 switch (auto source_type = source().type())
17087 {
17088 case node_type::table:
17089 decrease_indent(); // so root kvps and tables have the same indent
17090 print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&source()));
17091 break;
17092
17093 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&source())); break;
17094
17095 case node_type::string: print_yaml_string(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&source())); break;
17096
17097 default: print_value(source(), source_type);
17098 }
17099 }
17100}
